{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NVVnKtpffj8vVWUMwcyFsH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ# SOAR-ARC Inner Loop ÔÇö Claude Code Autonomous Development Instructions\n     2Ôćĺ\n     3Ôćĺ> This file is the only instruction document that Claude Code reads at the start of each session.\n     4Ôćĺ> When starting a session, you must read this entire file before proceeding.\n     5Ôćĺ\n     6Ôćĺ---\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8Ôćĺ## Repository\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10Ôćĺ- **GitHub**: https://github.com/Albertree/SOAR-ARC-test.git\n    11Ôćĺ- **Local root**: current working directory\n    12Ôćĺ\n    13Ôćĺ---\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15Ôćĺ## Mission (unchanging)\n    16Ôćĺ\n    17Ôćĺ```\n    18ÔćĺOutput \"CORRECT\" when running python run_task.py\n    19Ôćĺ```\n    20Ôćĺ\n    21ÔćĺTarget task: `08ed6ac7`\n    22ÔćĺSuccess = accurately predict the test output grid for this task.\n    23Ôćĺ\n    24ÔćĺThis is the completion criterion for inner loop stage 1.\n    25ÔćĺImprove the code each session until CORRECT is output.\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ---\n    28Ôćĺ\n    29Ôćĺ## Do NOT Modify Under Any Circumstances\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31Ôćĺ```\n    32Ôćĺdata/          ÔćÉ ARC data source (read-only)\n    33ÔćĺPROMPT.md      ÔćÉ This file itself\n    34Ôćĺ```\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36ÔćĺAll other files may be modified.\n    37Ôćĺ\n    38Ôćĺ---\n    39Ôćĺ\n    40Ôćĺ## Current Implementation Status\n    41Ôćĺ\n    42Ôćĺ### Completed\n    43Ôćĺ| Layer | File | Status |\n    44Ôćĺ|-------|------|--------|\n    45Ôćĺ| ARCKG base layer | `ARCKG/*.py` | Done |\n    46Ôćĺ| DSL tools | `procedural_memory/DSL/*.py` | Done |\n    47Ôćĺ| Task loading | `managers/arc_manager.py` | Done |\n    48Ôćĺ| Evaluation env | `arc2_env/arc_environment.py` | Done |\n    49Ôćĺ| SOAR structure | `agent/*.py` | Skeleton complete |\n    50Ôćĺ| Entry point | `run_task.py` | Done |\n    51Ôćĺ\n    52Ôćĺ### Incomplete (this is the target of the current mission)\n    53Ôćĺ| Layer | Issue |\n    54Ôćĺ|-------|-------|\n    55Ôćĺ| SOAR operator implementation | `substate-progress` is a placeholder ÔÇö does nothing |\n    56Ôćĺ| WM slots | Core slots like `^focus-level`, `^focus-parent-id` are unused |\n    57Ôćĺ| compare integration | `ARCKG/comparison.py`'s `compare()` is not called from the agent loop |\n    58Ôćĺ| predict/submit | No logic to write prediction results to the output-link |\n    59Ôćĺ\n    60Ôćĺ---\n    61Ôćĺ\n    62Ôćĺ## System Design Principles\n    63Ôćĺ\n    64Ôćĺ### ARCKG 5-Level Hierarchy\n    65Ôćĺ\n    66Ôćĺ```\n    67ÔćĺTASK (T{hex})\n    68Ôćĺ ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ PAIR (P{n} / Pa for test)\n    69Ôćĺ      ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ GRID (G0=input, G1=output)\n    70Ôćĺ           ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ OBJECT (O{n})\n    71Ôćĺ                ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ PIXEL (X{n})\n    72Ôćĺ```\n    73Ôćĺ\n    74Ôćĺ- Node = folder, Edge = JSON file\n    75Ôćĺ- Relations are lazily generated ÔÇö `compare()` is called only when needed\n    76Ôćĺ- Comparison results are stored under `semantic_memory/`\n    77Ôćĺ\n    78Ôćĺ### SOAR Decision Cycle\n    79Ôćĺ\n    80Ôćĺ```\n    81ÔćĺEach cycle:\n    82Ôćĺ  1. Elaborate  ÔÇö Repeat ElaborationRules until fixed-point\n    83Ôćĺ  2. Propose    ÔÇö ProductionRules collect operator candidates\n    84Ôćĺ  3. Select     ÔÇö Choose one based on PREFERENCE_ORDER\n    85Ôćĺ  4. Apply      ÔÇö Call operator.effect(wm)\n    86Ôćĺ\n    87ÔćĺImpasse conditions:\n    88Ôćĺ  - No WM change (no-change) Ôćĺ create substate\n    89Ôćĺ  - Operator failure         Ôćĺ create substate\n    90Ôćĺ  - No candidates            Ôćĺ create substate\n    91Ôćĺ```\n    92Ôćĺ\n    93Ôćĺ### Operator Design Intent (implementation target)\n    94Ôćĺ\n    95Ôćĺ| Operator | Intent | What to write to WM |\n    96Ôćĺ|----------|--------|---------------------|\n    97Ôćĺ| `solve-task` | Top-level goal representation. No WM change Ôćĺ trigger no-change impasse | Nothing (intentional) |\n    98Ôćĺ| `deepen` | Move focus one level down | `^focus-level`, `^focus-ids` |\n    99Ôćĺ| `compare-within-parent` | Compare G0 vs G1 within a single PAIR | `^last-comparison` |\n   100Ôćĺ| `compare-siblings` | Compare sibling nodes at the same level (e.g., P0 vs P1) | `^last-comparison` |\n   101Ôćĺ| `note-imbalance` | Detect structural imbalance | `^imbalance`, `^imbalance-kind` |\n   102Ôćĺ| `extract-invariants` | Extract common patterns from comparison results | `^invariant-chunk` |\n   103Ôćĺ| `generalize` | Create abstract rules | Save to `procedural_memory` |\n   104Ôćĺ| `predict` | Apply rules to test input | Predicted grid on output-link |\n   105Ôćĺ| `submit` | Submit prediction Ôćĺ complete goal | `^goal-satisfied true` |\n   106Ôćĺ\n   107Ôćĺ**Prohibited**: Do not use TASK, PAIR, GRID, OBJECT, PIXEL directly in operator names/docstrings.\n   108ÔćĺLevels are expressed only through the `^focus-level` WM slot value.\n   109Ôćĺ\n   110Ôćĺ---\n   111Ôćĺ\n   112Ôćĺ## How the Agent Solves the Problem (implementation reference)\n   113Ôćĺ\n   114ÔćĺBelow is a concrete exploration flow based on task `08ed6ac7`.\n   115ÔćĺUse this as a reference to implement operators that actually perform this flow.\n   116Ôćĺ\n   117Ôćĺ### Step 1 ÔÇö Receive TASK\n   118Ôćĺ- Load task with `ARCManager` Ôćĺ build ARCKG (already working)\n   119Ôćĺ- Inject into WM input-link with `inject_arc_task(task, wm)` (already working)\n   120Ôćĺ- `solve-task` operator proposed Ôćĺ no WM change Ôćĺ no-change impasse Ôćĺ S2 created\n   121Ôćĺ\n   122Ôćĺ### Step 2 ÔÇö Check TASK properties\n   123Ôćĺ- `deepen` operator proposed in S2\n   124Ôćĺ- Write `^focus-level = \"TASK\"` to WM\n   125Ôćĺ- Read `E_T{hex}.json` to check TASK properties (`number_of_pairs`, etc.)\n   126Ôćĺ\n   127Ôćĺ### Step 3 ÔÇö Compare with other TASKs in semantic_memory\n   128Ôćĺ- On first run, no other TASKs exist Ôćĺ this step can be skipped\n   129Ôćĺ- If other TASKs exist in semantic_memory, run `compare-siblings`\n   130Ôćĺ\n   131Ôćĺ### Step 4 ÔÇö Descend to PAIR level\n   132Ôćĺ- TASK properties alone cannot achieve the goal Ôćĺ impasse\n   133Ôćĺ- `deepen` Ôćĺ `^focus-level = \"PAIR\"`\n   134Ôćĺ- Check all PAIR properties (`number_of_grids`, example vs test distinction)\n   135Ôćĺ\n   136Ôćĺ### Step 5 ÔÇö Compare between PAIRs\n   137Ôćĺ- `compare-siblings` (P0 vs Pa)\n   138Ôćĺ- Result: Pa's grid_count = 1 Ôëá P0's grid_count = 2\n   139Ôćĺ- `note-imbalance` Ôćĺ `^imbalance-kind = \"grid_count\"`\n   140Ôćĺ- Set goal: make Pa's grid_count = 2 = generate output GRID\n   141Ôćĺ\n   142Ôćĺ### Step 6 ÔÇö Descend to GRID level\n   143Ôćĺ- `deepen` Ôćĺ `^focus-level = \"GRID\"`\n   144Ôćĺ- Compare G0 (input) vs G1 (output) within P0: `compare-within-parent`\n   145Ôćĺ- Call `compare()` Ôćĺ generate `E_P0G0-P0G1.json`\n   146Ôćĺ- Check GRID property (color, size, contents) differences/commonalities\n   147Ôćĺ\n   148Ôćĺ### Step 7 ÔÇö Compare with other PAIR GRIDs\n   149Ôćĺ- `compare-siblings` (P0G0 vs P1G0, P0G1 vs P1G1)\n   150Ôćĺ- Discovery: all GRID sizes identical, inputs share same colors, outputs share same colors\n   151Ôćĺ- Conclusion: Pa's output GRID size = example output size, color = example output color\n   152Ôćĺ- However, contents cannot be predicted yet Ôćĺ new goal: predict contents\n   153Ôćĺ\n   154Ôćĺ### Step 8 ÔÇö Descend to OBJECT level\n   155Ôćĺ- `deepen` Ôćĺ `^focus-level = \"OBJECT\"`\n   156Ôćĺ- Check all Object properties in P0G0\n   157Ôćĺ- Check all Object properties in P0G1\n   158Ôćĺ- `compare-within-parent` (P0G0 objects vs P0G1 objects, 1:1 mapping)\n   159Ôćĺ- Result: Object with area=9 color=5 Ôćĺ transformed to area=9 color=1 (score 7/8)\n   160Ôćĺ- Generate temporary program Ôćĺ apply to P0G0 Ôćĺ compare with P0G1\n   161Ôćĺ\n   162Ôćĺ### Step 9 ÔÇö Compare OBJECTs from other PAIRs\n   163Ôćĺ- Repeat the same process for P1G0, P1G1\n   164Ôćĺ- Discovery: color=5 Ôćĺ color=1 pattern exists in P1 as well\n   165Ôćĺ- However, criteria for which Object is selected in each PAIR are needed\n   166Ôćĺ\n   167Ôćĺ### Step 10 ÔÇö Extract Object selection criteria\n   168Ôćĺ- Search for common internal relations among transformed Objects in P0G0 and P1G0\n   169Ôćĺ- Discovery: transformed Object is the one with the largest area among Objects with the same color\n   170Ôćĺ- This becomes the selection criterion Ôćĺ `extract-invariants`\n   171Ôćĺ- `^invariant-chunk = \"select object where color=X and area=max among siblings\"`\n   172Ôćĺ\n   173Ôćĺ### Step 11 ÔÇö Rule generation\n   174Ôćĺ- `generalize` operator\n   175Ôćĺ- Rule: \"Transform the color of the Object with max area among Objects with color=X to Y\"\n   176Ôćĺ- X, Y are values extracted from PAIR comparisons\n   177Ôćĺ\n   178Ôćĺ### Step 12 ÔÇö Apply to test input\n   179Ôćĺ- `predict` operator\n   180Ôćĺ- Apply rule to Pa's G0 (input only)\n   181Ôćĺ- Generate output GRID\n   182Ôćĺ\n   183Ôćĺ### Step 13 ÔÇö Submit\n   184Ôćĺ- `submit` operator\n   185Ôćĺ- `^goal-satisfied true`\n   186Ôćĺ- `run_task.py` Ôćĺ confirm \"CORRECT\"\n   187Ôćĺ\n   188Ôćĺ---\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ## Per-Session Procedure\n   191Ôćĺ\n   192Ôćĺ### At session start\n   193Ôćĺ\n   194Ôćĺ```bash\n   195Ôćĺ# 1. Check previous session logs\n   196Ôćĺcat logs/session_log.md | tail -50\n   197Ôćĺ\n   198Ôćĺ# 2. Check current status\n   199Ôćĺpython run_task.py\n   200Ôćĺ\n   201Ôćĺ# 3. Analyze errors/output, then set goals for this session\n   202Ôćĺ```\n   203Ôćĺ\n   204Ôćĺ### During session\n   205Ôćĺ\n   206Ôćĺ- Implement one operator or rule at a time\n   207Ôćĺ- After implementation, always run `python run_task.py` to verify direction\n   208Ôćĺ- If errors occur, analyze error messages to identify causes and fix them\n   209Ôćĺ\n   210Ôćĺ### At session end (must follow this order)\n   211Ôćĺ\n   212Ôćĺ```bash\n   213Ôćĺ# 1. Final run_task.py execution and capture results\n   214Ôćĺpython run_task.py 2>&1 | tee /tmp/session_result.txt\n   215Ôćĺ\n   216Ôćĺ# 2. Write session log (format below)\n   217Ôćĺ# Append to logs/session_log.md\n   218Ôćĺ\n   219Ôćĺ# 3. git add & commit & pus