F items from `^last-comparison`\n   274Ôćĺ   - Write `^imbalance-kind` to WM\n   275Ôćĺ\n   276Ôćĺ6. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `ExtractInvariantsOperator`\n   277Ôćĺ   - Extract COMM patterns Ôćĺ `^invariant-chunk`\n   278Ôćĺ\n   279Ôćĺ7. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `PredictOperator`\n   280Ôćĺ   - Apply invariant + diff patterns to test input\n   281Ôćĺ\n   282Ôćĺ8. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `SubmitOperator`\n   283Ôćĺ   - Write result to output-link\n   284Ôćĺ   - `^goal-satisfied true`\n   285Ôćĺ\n   286Ôćĺ---\n   287Ôćĺ\n   288Ôćĺ## Key File Structure\n   289Ôćĺ\n   290Ôćĺ```\n   291Ôćĺagent/\n   292Ôćĺ  cycle.py          ÔćÉ run_cycle() ÔÇö modify with caution\n   293Ôćĺ  wm.py             ÔćÉ WorkingMemory ÔÇö modify with caution\n   294Ôćĺ  active_operators.py ÔćÉ Core implementation target\n   295Ôćĺ  rules.py            ÔćÉ Core implementation target\n   296Ôćĺ  elaboration_rules.pyÔćÉ Secondary implementation target\n   297Ôćĺ  preferences.py      ÔćÉ PREFERENCE_ORDER (operator priorities)\n   298Ôćĺ\n   299ÔćĺARCKG/\n   300Ôćĺ  comparison.py     ÔćÉ compare() ÔÇö already complete, just needs to be called\n   301Ôćĺ  task.py, pair.py, grid.py, object.py, pixel.py\n   302Ôćĺ\n   303Ôćĺmanagers/\n   304Ôćĺ  arc_manager.py    ÔćÉ ARCManager ÔÇö already complete\n   305Ôćĺ\n   306Ôćĺrun_task.py         ÔćÉ Success criteria evaluation script (do not modify)\n   307Ôćĺ```\n   308Ôćĺ\n   309Ôćĺ---\n   310Ôćĺ\n   311Ôćĺ## Completion Condition\n   312Ôćĺ\n   313Ôćĺ```bash\n   314Ôćĺpython run_task.py\n   315Ôćĺ# When output contains \"CORRECT\", inner loop stage 1 is complete\n   316Ôćĺ# Ôćĺ Record \"MISSION COMPLETE\" in logs/session_log.md\n   317Ôćĺ# Ôćĺ git push\n   318Ôćĺ# Ôćĺ Loop terminated\n   319Ôćĺ```\n   320Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"d3905555-a7f0-4593-8d7a-ed056b08aba2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:32:50.250Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\PROMPT.md","content":"# SOAR-ARC Inner Loop ÔÇö Claude Code Autonomous Development Instructions\n\n> This file is the only instruction document that Claude Code reads at the start of each session.\n> When starting a session, you must read this entire file before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n## Repository\n\n- **GitHub**: https://github.com/Albertree/SOAR-ARC-test.git\n- **Local root**: current working directory\n\n---\n\n## Mission (unchanging)\n\n```\nOutput \"CORRECT\" when running python run_task.py\n```\n\nTarget task: `08ed6ac7`\nSuccess = accurately predict the test output grid for this task.\n\nThis is the completion criterion for inner loop stage 1.\nImprove the code each session until CORRECT is output.\n\n---\n\n## Do NOT Modify Under Any Circumstances\n\n```\ndata/          ÔćÉ ARC data source (read-only)\nPROMPT.md      ÔćÉ This file itself\n```\n\nAll other files may be modified.\n\n---\n\n## Current Implementation Status\n\n### Completed\n| Layer | File | Status |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| ARCKG base layer | `ARCKG/*.py` | Done |\n| DSL tools | `procedural_memory/DSL/*.py` | Done |\n| Task loading | `managers/arc_manager.py` | Done |\n| Evaluation env | `arc2_env/arc_environment.py` | Done |\n| SOAR structure | `agent/*.py` | Skeleton complete |\n| Entry point | `run_task.py` | Done |\n\n### Incomplete (this is the target of the current mission)\n| Layer | Issue |\n|-------|-------|\n| SOAR operator implementation | `substate-progress` is a placeholder ÔÇö does nothing |\n| WM slots | Core slots like `^focus-level`, `^focus-parent-id` are unused |\n| compare integration | `ARCKG/comparison.py`'s `compare()` is not called from the agent loop |\n| predict/submit | No logic to write prediction results to the output-link |\n\n---\n\n## System Design Principles\n\n### ARCKG 5-Level Hierarchy\n\n```\nTASK (T{hex})\n ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ PAIR (P{n} / Pa for test)\n      ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ GRID (G0=input, G1=output)\n           ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ OBJECT (O{n})\n                ÔööÔöÇÔöÇ PIXEL (X{n})\n```\n\n- Node = folder, Edge = JSON file\n- Relations are lazily generated ÔÇö `compare()` is called only when needed\n- Comparison results are stored under `semantic_memory/`\n\n### SOAR Decision Cycle\n\n```\nEach cycle:\n  1. Elaborate  ÔÇö Repeat ElaborationRules until fixed-point\n  2. Propose    ÔÇö ProductionRules collect operator candidates\n  3. Select     ÔÇö Choose one based on PREFERENCE_ORDER\n  4. Apply      ÔÇö Call operator.effect(wm)\n\nImpasse conditions:\n  - No WM change (no-change) Ôćĺ create substate\n  - Operator failure         Ôćĺ create substate\n  - No candidates            Ôćĺ create substate\n```\n\n### Operator Design Intent (implementation target)\n\n| Operator | Intent | What to write to WM |\n|----------|--------|---------------------|\n| `solve-task` | Top-level goal representation. No WM change Ôćĺ trigger no-change impasse | Nothing (intentional) |\n| `deepen` | Move focus one level down | `^focus-level`, `^focus-ids` |\n| `compare-within-parent` | Compare G0 vs G1 within a single PAIR | `^last-comparison` |\n| `compare-siblings` | Compare sibling nodes at the same level (e.g., P0 vs P1) | `^last-comparison` |\n| `note-imbalance` | Detect structural imbalance | `^imbalance`, `^imbalance-kind` |\n| `extract-invariants` | Extract common patterns from comparison results | `^invariant-chunk` |\n| `generalize` | Create abstract rules | Save to `procedural_memory` |\n| `predict` | Apply rules to test input | Predicted grid on output-link |\n| `submit` | Submit prediction Ôćĺ complete goal | `^goal-satisfied true` |\n\n**Prohibited**: Do not use TASK, PAIR, GRID, OBJECT, PIXEL directly in operator names/docstrings.\nLevels are expressed only through the `^focus-level` WM slot value.\n\n---\n\n## How the Agent Solves the Problem (implementation reference)\n\nBelow is a concrete exploration flow based on task `08ed6ac7`.\nUse this as a reference to implement operators that actually perform this flow.\n\n### Step 1 ÔÇö Receive TASK\n- Load task with `ARCManager` Ôćĺ build ARCKG (already working)\n- Inject into WM input-link with `inject_arc_task(task, wm)` (already working)\n- `solve-task` operator proposed Ôćĺ no WM change Ôćĺ no-change impasse Ôćĺ S2 created\n\n### Step 2 ÔÇö Check TASK properties\n- `deepen` operator proposed in S2\n- Write `^focus-level = \"TASK\"` to WM\n- Read `E_T{hex}.json` to check TASK properties (`number_of_pairs`, etc.)\n\n### Step 3 ÔÇö Compare with other TASKs in semantic_memory\n- On first run, no other TASKs exist Ôćĺ this step can be skipped\n- If other TASKs exist in semantic_memory, run `compare-siblings`\n\n### Step 4 ÔÇö Descend to PAIR level\n- TASK properties alone cannot achieve the goal Ôćĺ impasse\n- `deepen` Ôćĺ `^focus-level = \"PAIR\"`\n- Check all PAIR properties (`number_of_grids`, example vs test distinction)\n\n### Step 5 ÔÇö Compare between PAIRs\n- `compare-siblings` (P0 vs Pa)\n- Result: Pa's grid_count = 1 Ôëá P0's grid_count = 2\n- `note-imbalance` Ôćĺ `^imbalance-kind = \"grid_count\"`\n- Set goal: make Pa's grid_count = 2 = generate output GRID\n\n### Step 6 ÔÇö Descend to GRID level\n- `deepen` Ôćĺ `^focus-level = \"GRID\"`\n- Compare G0 (input) vs G1 (output) within P0: `compare-within-parent`\n- Call `compare()` Ôćĺ generate `E_P0G0-P0G1.json`\n- Check GRID property (color, size, contents) differences/commonalities\n\n### Step 7 ÔÇö Compare with other PAIR GRIDs\n- `compare-siblings` (P0G0 vs P1G0, P0G1 vs P1G1)\n- Discovery: all GRID sizes identical, inputs share same colors, outputs share same colors\n- Conclusion: Pa's output GRID size = example output size, color = example output color\n- However, contents cannot be predicted yet Ôćĺ new goal: predict contents\n\n### Step 8 ÔÇö Descend to OBJECT level\n- `deepen` Ôćĺ `^focus-level = \"OBJECT\"`\n- Check all Object properties in P0G0\n- Check all Object properties in P0G1\n- `compare-within-parent` (P0G0 objects vs P0G1 objects, 1:1 mapping)\n- Result: Object with area=9 color=5 Ôćĺ transformed to area=9 color=1 (score 7/8)\n- Generate temporary program Ôćĺ apply to P0G0 Ôćĺ compare with P0G1\n\n### Step 9 ÔÇö Compare OBJECTs from other PAIRs\n- Repeat the same process for P1G0, P1G1\n- Discovery: color=5 Ôćĺ color=1 pattern exists in P1 as well\n- However, criteria for which Object is selected in each PAIR are needed\n\n### Step 10 ÔÇö Extract Object selection criteria\n- Search for common internal relations among transformed Objects in P0G0 and P1G0\n- Discovery: transformed Object is the one with the largest area among Objects with the same color\n- This becomes the selection criterion Ôćĺ `extract-invariants`\n- `^invariant-chunk = \"select object where color=X and area=max among siblings\"`\n\n### Step 11 ÔÇö Rule generation\n- `generalize` operator\n- Rule: \"Transform the color of the Object with max area among Objects with color=X to Y\"\n- X, Y are values extracted from PAIR comparisons\n\n### Step 12 ÔÇö Apply to test input\n- `predict` operator\n- Apply rule to Pa's G0 (input only)\n- Generate output GRID\n\n### Step 13 ÔÇö Submit\n- `submit` operator\n- `^goal-satisfied true`\n- `run_task.py` Ôćĺ confirm \"CORRECT\"\n\n---\n\n## Per-Session Procedure\n\n### At session start\n\n```bash\n# 1. Check previous session logs\ncat logs/session_log.md | tail -50\n\n# 2. Check current status\npython run_task.py\n\n# 3. Analyze errors/output, then set goals for this session\n```\n\n### During session\n\n- Implement one operator or rule at a time\n- After implementation, always run `python run_task.py` to verify direction\n- If errors occur, analyze error messages to identify causes and fix them\n\n### At session end (must follow this order)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Final run_task.py execution and capture results\npython run_task.py 2>&1 | tee /tmp/session_result.txt\n\n# 2. Write session log (format below)\n# Append to logs/session_log.md\n\n# 3. git add & commit & push\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"Session N: <one-line summary>\"\ngit push origin main\n```\n\n---\n\n## Session Log Format\n\n**Append** to the file `logs/session_log.md` in the format below.\n(Create the file if it does not exist)\n\n```markdown\n---\n## Session N ÔÇö YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM\n\n### This session's goal\n(What was intended)\n\n### Modified files\n- `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implemented deepen operator (reason: ...)\n- `agent/rules.py` ÔÇö Added siblings-ready rule (reason: ...)\n\n### run_task.py result\n(Paste key parts of execution output)\n\n### Discoveries / Gotchas\n(Unexpected findings, caveats, reasons for getting stuck)\n\n### Starting point for next session\n(Stopped here, next session should do this)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Priority (refer to when stuck)\n\n1. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `DeepenOperator`\n   - Lower `^focus-level` WM slot by one step\n   - Record list of node IDs at that level in `^focus-ids`\n\n2. `agent/rules.py` ÔÇö Implement `top-scope-no-detail` rule\n   - Condition: no `^focus-level`, `^current-task` exists\n   - Propose: `deepen`\n\n3. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `CompareWithinParentOperator`\n   - Call `compare()` from `ARCKG/comparison.py`\n   - Write result to WM `^last-comparison`\n\n4. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `CompareSiblingsOperator`\n   - Sequentially compare sibling nodes under the same parent\n\n5. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `NoteImbalanceOperator`\n   - Detect DIFF items from `^last-comparison`\n   - Write `^imbalance-kind` to WM\n\n6. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `ExtractInvariantsOperator`\n   - Extract COMM patterns Ôćĺ `^invariant-chunk`\n\n7. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `PredictOperator`\n   - Apply invariant + diff patterns to test input\n\n8. `agent/active_operators.py` ÔÇö Implement `SubmitOperator`\n   - Write result to output-link\n   - `^goal-satisfied true`\n\n---\n\n## Key File Structure\n\n```\nagent/\n  cycle.py      