{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GhHtXMHMM3DnsG6i8MeR3t","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n     2Ôćĺactive_operators ÔÇö SOAR Operator implementations.\n     3Ôćĺ\n     4ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n     5Ôćĺ[SOAR MANDATORY] Each operator follows the precondition + effect interface.\n     6Ôćĺ                 effect updates WM. cycle determines success/failure/no-change by exception/wme changes.\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8Ôćĺ[DESIGN FREE] Which operators to have, names, precondition conditions, effect content.\n     9Ôćĺ              Compare function (compare_fn) and generalize function (generalize_fn) can be externally injected.\n    10Ôćĺ\n    11ÔćĺThe operators in this module are designed to correspond to the following six cognitive-level operations.\n    12Ôćĺ\n    13Ôćĺ    1. compare  (target_a, target_b, level)\n    14Ôćĺ    2. collect  (scope, relation_type)\n    15Ôćĺ    3. generalize(targets)\n    16Ôćĺ    4. descend  (target, from_level, to_level)\n    17Ôćĺ    5. predict  (test_input, rule_ref)\n    18Ôćĺ    6. verify   (predicted_output, constraints)\n    19Ôćĺ\n    20ÔćĺThe mapping between concrete classes is as follows.\n    21Ôćĺ\n    22Ôćĺ    - CompareOperator         Ôćĺ compare\n    23Ôćĺ    - ExtractPatternOperator  Ôćĺ collect\n    24Ôćĺ    - GeneralizeOperator      Ôćĺ generalize\n    25Ôćĺ    - DescendOperator         Ôćĺ descend\n    26Ôćĺ    - PredictOperator         Ôćĺ predict\n    27Ôćĺ    - SubmitOperator/VerifyOperator Ôćĺ verify\n    28Ôćĺ\n    29ÔćĺThat is, while maintaining the SOAR-style Operator interface,\n    30Ôćĺthe high-level operator repertoire from the user's perspective is directly reflected.\n    31ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n    32Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n    33Ôćĺ\n    34Ôćĺfrom agent.operators import Operator\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36Ôćĺ\n    37Ôćĺclass SolveTaskOperator(Operator):\n    38Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    39Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] High-level operator for solving the top-level ARC task.\n    40Ôćĺ\n    41Ôćĺ    INTENT:\n    42Ôćĺ        - When (S1 ^current-task <hex>) exists, organizes sub-operators such as\n    43Ôćĺ          compare/collect/generalize/descend to solve the task.\n    44Ôćĺ        - At the current stage, only secures the interface (name, position) without concrete logic.\n    45Ôćĺ\n    46Ôćĺ    Future:\n    47Ôćĺ        - precondition: When current-task exists in S1 and goal is not yet complete.\n    48Ôćĺ        - effect: Performs part of the solve-task pipeline during one decision cycle.\n    49Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    50Ôćĺ\n    51Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n    52Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"solve-task\")\n    53Ôćĺ        self.proposal_preference = \"+\"\n    54Ôćĺ\n    55Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n    56Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] To be extended later to check S1^current-task, goal state, etc.\"\"\"\n    57Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"SolveTaskOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n    58Ôćĺ\n    59Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n    60Ôćĺ        \"\"\"Abstract operator: intentionally no WM change.\n    61Ôćĺ\n    62Ôćĺ        From the Soar perspective, solve-task only presents a high-level goal,\n    63Ôćĺ        and actual state changes are performed by concrete operators in sub-substates (S2...).\n    64Ôćĺ        Therefore, no WM modification is done here.\n    65Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n    66Ôćĺ        return\n    67Ôćĺ\n    68Ôćĺ\n    69Ôćĺclass SubstateProgressOperator(Operator):\n    70Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    71Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] Minimal result to resolve operator no-change impasse in a substate.\n    72Ôćĺ\n    73Ôćĺ    Adds a short summary WME to the superstate S1, so that subsequent cycles\n    74Ôćĺ    reflect the change in the superstate WM. (Placeholder before full i-support retract.)\n    75Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    76Ôćĺ\n    77Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n    78Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"substate-progress\")\n    79Ôćĺ        self.proposal_preference = \"+\"\n    80Ôćĺ\n    81Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n    82Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\n    83Ôćĺ            \"SubstateProgressOperator.precondition() not implemented.\"\n    84Ôćĺ        )\n    85Ôćĺ\n    86Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n    87Ôćĺ        attr = wm.active.get(\"attribute\")\n    88Ôćĺ        wm.s1[\"substate-resolution\"] = f\"handled-no-change:{attr}\"\n    89Ôćĺ\n    90Ôćĺ\n    91Ôćĺclass SelectTargetOperator(Operator):\n    92Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    93Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n    94Ôćĺ    INTENT: (Not implemented) After selecting comparison targets, reflects pending comparison items in WM.\n    95Ôćĺ            Does not use dedicated dict/helpers for agenda/pending.\n    96Ôćĺ            Does not know the concrete comparison target types.\n    97Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not perform the comparison itself ÔÇö only queue movement.\n    98Ôćĺ              Do not directly reference wm.task.\n    99Ôćĺ    precondition: elaborated[\"needs_target_selection\"] == True\n   100Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   101Ôćĺ\n   102Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   103Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"select_target\")\n   104Ôćĺ\n   105Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   106Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n   107Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"SelectTargetOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n   108Ôćĺ\n   109Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n   110Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   111Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE]\n   112Ôćĺ        1. Select comparison targets\n   113Ôćĺ        2. Reflect pending comparison facts in WM (triplet)\n   114Ôćĺ        3. ...\n   115Ôćĺ        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n   116Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   117Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"SelectTargetOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n   118Ôćĺ\n   119Ôćĺ\n   120Ôćĺclass CompareOperator(Operator):\n   121Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   122Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n   123Ôćĺ    INTENT: Performs one pending comparison and adds the result to WM as a triplet.\n   124Ôćĺ            Comparison function uses external injection (compare_fn) or default.\n   125Ôćĺ            CompareOperator does not know what the items are.\n   126Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not process multiple items at once from the queue ÔÇö 1 call = 1 comparison.\n   127Ôćĺ              Do not hardcode a specific comparison library in the class.\n   128Ôćĺ    precondition: elaborated[\"has_pending_comparison\"] == True\n   129Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   130Ôćĺ\n   131Ôćĺ    def __init__(self, compare_fn=None):\n   132Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   133Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE] compare_fn: (node_a, node_b, context) Ôćĺ result.\n   134Ôćĺ                       None uses the default comparison function.\n   135Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   136Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"compare\")\n   137Ôćĺ        self._compare_fn = compare_fn\n   138Ôćĺ\n   139Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   140Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n   141Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"CompareOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n   142Ôćĺ\n   143Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n   144Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   145Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE]\n   146Ôćĺ        1. Obtain pending comparison item\n   147Ôćĺ        2. Call self._compare_fn(node_a, node_b, context)\n   148Ôćĺ        3. Reflect comparison result in WM (triplet)\n   149Ôćĺ        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n   150Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   151Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"CompareOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n   152Ôćĺ\n   153Ôćĺ\n   154Ôćĺclass ExtractPatternOperator(Operator):\n   155Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   156Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n   157Ôćĺ    INTENT: Organizes COMM/DIFF patterns from comparison results into WM triplets.\n   158Ôćĺ            On failure, reflects a goal for deeper analysis in WM.\n   159Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not implement COMM/DIFF determination logic here ÔÇö only read the result's type field.\n   160Ôćĺ    precondition: elaborated[\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\"] == True\n   161Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   162Ôćĺ\n   163Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   164Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"extract_pattern\")\n   165Ôćĺ\n   166Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   167Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n   168Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"ExtractPatternOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n   169Ôćĺ\n   170Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n   171Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   172Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE]\n   173Ôćĺ        Serves the role corresponding to collect(scope, relation_type)\n   174Ôćĺ        in the compare/collect/generalize pipeline.\n   175Ôćĺ\n   176Ôćĺ        1. Iterate comparison results\n   177Ôćĺ        2. Record COMM/DIFF as WM triplets\n   178Ôćĺ        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n   179Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   180Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"ExtractPatternOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n   181Ôćĺ\n   182Ôćĺ\n   183Ôćĺclass DescendOperator(Operator):\n   184Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   185Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n   186Ôćĺ    INTENT: When an impasse occurs at a higher level such as GRID/OBJECT/PIXEL analysis,\n   187Ôćĺ            implements descend(target, from_level, to_level) by\n   188Ôćĺ            pulling lower-level nodes/relations into WM to enable further comparisons.\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ    This operation is implemented in the SOAR perspective as substate creation or\n   191Ôćĺ    comparison_agenda extension for impasse resolution.\n   192Ôćĺ\n   193Ôćĺ    Example conceptual flow:\n   194Ôćĺ        - from_level analysis is insufficient Ôćĺ elaborated[\"needs_descend\"] = True\n   195Ôćĺ        - DescendOperator.effect:\n   196Ôćĺ            1) wm.push_substate(...) or\n   197Ôćĺ            2) Reflect more granular comparison tasks in WM\n   198Ôćĺ\n   199Ôćĺ    precondition: elaborated[\"needs_descend\"] == True (design choice)\n   200Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   201Ôćĺ\n   202Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   203Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"descend\")\n   204Ôćĺ\n   205Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   206Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n   207Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"DescendOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n   208Ôćĺ\n   209Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n   210Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   211Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE]\n   212Ôćĺ        1. Read current focus/impasse information to interpret from_level, to_level\n   213Ôćĺ        2. Add lower-level comparison tasks for target pair/objects to the agenda or\n   214Ôćĺ           call wm.push_substate(...) to open a subgoal if needed.\n   215Ôćĺ        3. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n   216Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   217Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"DescendOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n   218Ôćĺ\n   219Ôćĺ\n   220Ôćĺclass GeneralizeOperator(Operator):\n   221Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   222Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n   223Ôćĺ    INTENT: Passes invariant/difference patterns collected in WM to a generalization function\n   224Ôćĺ            to generate abstract rules and add them to wm.active_rules.\n   225Ôćĺ            Generalization function and LTM save function use external injection or defaults.\n   226Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not hardcode a specific generalization module in the class.\n   227Ôćĺ    precondition: elaborated[\"ready_for_generalization\"] == True\n   228Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   229Ôćĺ\n   230Ôćĺ    def __init__(self, generalize_fn=None, save_fn=None):\n   231Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   232Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE] generalize_fn: (invariants, diff_patterns) Ôćĺ rule dict.\n   233Ôćĺ                       save_fn: rule dict Ôćĺ LTM ref str.\n   234Ôćĺ                       None uses the default implementation.\n   235Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   236Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"generalize\")\n   237Ôćĺ        self._generalize_fn = generalize_fn\n   238Ôćĺ        self._save_fn = save_fn\n   239Ôćĺ\n   240Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   241Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n   242Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"GeneralizeOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n   243Ôćĺ\n   244Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n   245Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   246Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE]\n   247Ôćĺ        1. self._generalize_fn(invariant/difference information)\n   248Ôćĺ        2. self._save_fn(rule) Ôćĺ LTM ref path\n   249Ôćĺ        3. Add {\"ref\": path, \"confidence\": ...} to wm.active_rules\n   250Ôćĺ        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n   251Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   252Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"GeneralizeOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n   253Ôćĺ\n   254Ôćĺ\n   255Ôćĺclass PredictOperator(Operator):\n   256Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   257Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n   258Ôćĺ    INTENT: Applies the highest confidence rule from wm.active_rules to a pending test subgoal\n   259Ôćĺ            to predict output and update goal.subgoals and found.\n   260Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not try multiple rules in parallel ÔÇö single deterministic prediction.\n   261Ôćĺ    precondition: elaborated[\"ready_for_prediction\"] == True\n   262Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   263Ôćĺ\n   264Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   265Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"predict\")\n   266Ôćĺ\n   267Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   268Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n   269Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"PredictOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n   270Ôćĺ\n   271Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n   272Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   273Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE]\n   274Ôćĺ        1. Select one pending test subgoal\n   275Ôćĺ        2. Select the highest confidence rule from wm.active_rules\n   276Ôćĺ        3. Apply rule to test input Ôćĺ derive output\n   277Ôćĺ        4. Mark the test subgoal as solved + record in found\n   278Ôćĺ        5. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n   279Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   280Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"PredictOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n   281Ôćĺ\n   282Ôćĺ\n   283Ôćĺclass SubmitOperator(Operator):\n   284Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   285Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] The existence and precondition of this operator.\n   286Ôćĺ    [SOAR MANDATORY] There must be a final step that satisfies the goal_satisfied condition.\n   287Ôćĺ    INTENT: Sets op_status = \"success\" when elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"] == True.\n   288Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not perform actual scoring ÔÇö that is ARCEnvironment's responsibility.\n   289Ôćĺ    precondition: elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"] == True\n   290Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   291Ôćĺ\n   292Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   293Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"submit\")\n   294Ôćĺ\n   295Ôćĺ    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   296Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n   297Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"SubmitOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n   298Ôćĺ\n   299Ôćĺ    def effect(self, wm):\n   300Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   301Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE]\n   302Ôćĺ        Corresponds to the verify(predicted_output, constraints) step.\n   303Ôćĺ        When all test subgoals are resolved (elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"])\n   304Ôćĺ        and internal constraints are deemed satisfied,\n   305Ôćĺ        sets op_status = \"success\" to satisfy goal_satisfied.\n   306Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   307Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"SubmitOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n   308Ôćĺ\n   309Ôćĺ\n   310Ôćĺclass VerifyOperator(SubmitOperator):\n   311Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   312Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] Alias operator for the verify operation.\n   313Ôćĺ\n   314Ôćĺ    INTENT: Implements verify(predicted_output, constraints) at the cognitive level\n   315Ôćĺ            using the same mechanism as SubmitOperator at the SOAR operator level,\n   316Ôćĺ            while expressing the pipeline more explicitly through the name difference.\n   317Ôćĺ\n   318Ôćĺ    Implementation-wise, inherits SubmitOperator and uses the same precondition/effect.\n   319Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   320Ôćĺ\n   321Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   322Ôćĺ        super().__init__()\n   323Ôćĺ        # Reset name to \"verify\" to allow distinction in PREFERENCE_ORDER, etc.\n   324Ôćĺ        self.name = \"verify\"\n   325Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"c2ff3ded-0305-4aca-8f92-30f198cf56da","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:33:02.798Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\agent\\active_operators.py","content":"\"\"\"\nactive_operators ÔÇö SOAR Operator implementations.\n\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n[SOAR MANDATORY] Each operator follows the precondition + effect interface.\n                 effect updates WM. cycle determines success/failure/no-change by exception/wme changes.\n\n[DESIGN FREE] Which operators to have, names, precondition conditions, effect content.\n              Compare function (compare_fn) and generalize function (generalize_fn) can be externally injected.\n\nThe operators in this module are designed to correspond to the following six cognitive-level operations.\n\n    1. compare  (target_a, target_b, level)\n    2. collect  (scope, relation_type)\n    3. generalize(targets)\n    4. descend  (target, from_level, to_level)\n    5. predict  (test_input, rule_ref)\n    6. verify   (predicted_output, constraints)\n\nThe mapping between concrete classes is as follows.\n\n    - CompareOperator         Ôćĺ compare\n    - ExtractPatternOperator  Ôćĺ collect\n    - GeneralizeOperator      Ôćĺ generalize\n    - DescendOperator         Ôćĺ descend\n    - PredictOperator         Ôćĺ predict\n    - SubmitOperator/VerifyOperator Ôćĺ verify\n\nThat is, while maintaining the SOAR-style Operator interface,\nthe high-level operator repertoire from the user's perspective is directly reflected.\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom agent.operators import Operator\n\n\nclass SolveTaskOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] High-level operator for solving the top-level ARC task.\n\n    INTENT:\n        - When (S1 ^current-task <hex>) exists, organizes sub-operators such as\n          compare/collect/generalize/descend to solve the task.\n        - At the current stage, only secures the interface (name, position) without concrete logic.\n\n    Future:\n        - precondition: When current-task exists in S1 and goal is not yet complete.\n        - effect: Performs part of the solve-task pipeline during one decision cycle.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__(\"solve-task\")\n        self.proposal_preference = \"+\"\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] To be extended later to check S1^current-task, goal state, etc.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"SolveTaskOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"Abstract operator: intentionally no WM change.\n\n        From the Soar perspective, solve-task only presents a high-level goal,\n        and actual state changes are performed by concrete operators in sub-substates (S2...).\n        Therefore, no WM modification is done here.\n        \"\"\"\n        return\n\n\nclass SubstateProgressOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] Minimal result to resolve operator no-change impasse in a substate.\n\n    Adds a short summary WME to the superstate S1, so that subsequent cycles\n    reflect the change in the superstate WM. (Placeholder before full i-support retract.)\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__(\"substate-progress\")\n        self.proposal_preference = \"+\"\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\n            \"SubstateProgressOperator.precondition() not implemented.\"\n        )\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        attr = wm.active.get(\"attribute\")\n        wm.s1[\"substate-resolution\"] = f\"handled-no-change:{attr}\"\n\n\nclass SelectTargetOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n    INTENT: (Not implemented) After selecting comparison targets, reflects pending comparison items in WM.\n            Does not use dedicated dict/helpers for agenda/pending.\n            Does not know the concrete comparison target types.\n    MUST NOT: Do not perform the comparison itself ÔÇö only queue movement.\n              Do not directly reference wm.task.\n    precondition: elaborated[\"needs_target_selection\"] == True\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__(\"select_target\")\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"SelectTargetOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE]\n        1. Select comparison targets\n        2. Reflect pending comparison facts in WM (triplet)\n        3. ...\n        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"SelectTargetOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n\n\nclass CompareOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n    INTENT: Performs one pending comparison and adds the result to WM as a triplet.\n            Comparison function uses external injection (compare_fn) or default.\n            CompareOperator does not know what the items are.\n    MUST NOT: Do not process multiple items at once from the queue ÔÇö 1 call = 1 comparison.\n              Do not hardcode a specific comparison library in the class.\n    precondition: elaborated[\"has_pending_comparison\"] == True\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, compare_fn=None):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE] compare_fn: (node_a, node_b, context) Ôćĺ result.\n                       None uses the default comparison function.\n        \"\"\"\n        super().__init__(\"compare\")\n        self._compare_fn = compare_fn\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"CompareOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE]\n        1. Obtain pending comparison item\n        2. Call self._compare_fn(node_a, node_b, context)\n        3. Reflect comparison result in WM (triplet)\n        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"CompareOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n\n\nclass ExtractPatternOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n    INTENT: Organizes COMM/DIFF patterns from comparison results into WM triplets.\n            On failure, reflects a goal for deeper analysis in WM.\n    MUST NOT: Do not implement COMM/DIFF determination logic here ÔÇö only read the result's type field.\n    precondition: elaborated[\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\"] == True\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__(\"extract_pattern\")\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"ExtractPatternOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE]\n        Serves the role corresponding to collect(scope, relation_type)\n        in the compare/collect/generalize pipeline.\n\n        1. Iterate comparison results\n        2. Record COMM/DIFF as WM triplets\n        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"ExtractPatternOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n\n\nclass DescendOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n    INTENT: When an impasse occurs at a higher level such as GRID/OBJECT/PIXEL analysis,\n            implements descend(target, from_level, to_level) by\n            pulling lower-level nodes/relations into WM to enable further comparisons.\n\n    This operation is implemented in the SOAR perspective as substate creation or\n    comparison_agenda extension for impasse resolution.\n\n    Example conceptual flow:\n        - from_level analysis is insufficient Ôćĺ elaborated[\"needs_descend\"] = True\n        - DescendOperator.effect:\n            1) wm.push_substate(...) or\n            2) Reflect more granular comparison tasks in WM\n\n    precondition: elaborated[\"needs_descend\"] == True (design choice)\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__(\"descend\")\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"DescendOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE]\n        1. Read current focus/impasse information to interpret from_level, to_level\n        2. Add lower-level comparison tasks for target pair/objects to the agenda or\n           call wm.push_substate(...) to open a subgoal if needed.\n        3. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"DescendOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n\n\nclass GeneralizeOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n    INTENT: Passes invariant/difference patterns collected in WM to a generalization function\n            to generate abstract rules and add them to wm.active_rules.\n            Generalization function and LTM save function use external injection or defaults.\n    MUST NOT: Do not hardcode a specific generalization module in the class.\n    precondition: elaborated[\"ready_for_generalization\"] == True\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, generalize_fn=None, save_fn=None):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE] generalize_fn: (invariants, diff_patterns) Ôćĺ rule dict.\n                       save_fn: rule dict Ôćĺ LTM ref str.\n                       None uses the default implementation.\n        \"\"\"\n        super().__init__(\"generalize\")\n        self._generalize_fn = generalize_fn\n        self._save_fn = save_fn\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"GeneralizeOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE]\n        1. self._generalize_fn(invariant/difference information)\n        2. self._save_fn(rule) Ôćĺ LTM ref path\n        3. Add {\"ref\": path, \"confidence\": ...} to wm.active_rules\n        4. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"GeneralizeOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n\n\nclass PredictOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] The existence, precondition, and effect of this operator are all design choices.\n    INTENT: Applies the highest confidence rule from wm.active_rules to a pending test subgoal\n            to predict output and update goal.subgoals and found.\n    MUST NOT: Do not try multiple rules in parallel ÔÇö single deterministic prediction.\n    precondition: elaborated[\"ready_for_prediction\"] == True\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__(\"predict\")\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"PredictOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE]\n        1. Select one pending test subgoal\n        2. Select the highest confidence rule from wm.active_rules\n        3. Apply rule to test input Ôćĺ derive output\n        4. Mark the test subgoal as solved + record in found\n        5. op_status = \"success\" or \"failure\"\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"PredictOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n\n\nclass SubmitOperator(Operator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] The existence and precondition of this operator.\n    [SOAR MANDATORY] There must be a final step that satisfies the goal_satisfied condition.\n    INTENT: Sets op_status = \"success\" when elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"] == True.\n    MUST NOT: Do not perform actual scoring ÔÇö that is ARCEnvironment's responsibility.\n    precondition: elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"] == True\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__(\"submit\")\n\n    def precondition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE]\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"SubmitOperator.precondition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def effect(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE]\n        Corresponds to the verify(predicted_output, constraints) step.\n        When all test subgoals are resolved (elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"])\n        and internal constraints are deemed satisfied,\n        sets op_status = \"success\" to satisfy goal_satisfied.\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"SubmitOperator.effect() not implemented.\")\n\n\nclass VerifyOperator(SubmitOperator):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] Alias operator for the verify operation.\n\n    INTENT: Implements verify(predicted_output, constraints) at the cognitive level\n            using the same mechanism as SubmitOperator at the SOAR operator level,\n            while expressing the pipeline more explicitly through the name difference.\n\n    Implementation-wise, inherits SubmitOperator and uses the same precondition/effect.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        super().__init__()\n        # Reset name to \"verify\" to allow distinction in PREFERENCE_ORDER, etc.\n        self.name = \"verify\"\n","numLines":325,"startLine":1,"totalLines":325}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XckjrGeP4pk754yM3zUT6W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DLnjgNegNKjrE4xppMYrt4","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\agent\\rules.py"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7011,"cache_read_input_tokens":21074,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7011},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"2a60161c-a071-4677-a4b8-639443356fa9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DLnjgNegNKjrE4xppMYrt4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n     2Ôćĺrules ÔÇö Propose rules for SOAR Production Memory.\n     3Ôćĺ\n     4ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n     5Ôćĺ[SOAR MANDATORY] ProductionRule interface (condition + propose).\n     6Ôćĺ                 Proposer is the engine that iterates all rules to collect candidates.\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8Ôćĺ[DESIGN FREE] Which operator to propose for which WM state (entire rule content).\n     9Ôćĺ              Conditions in condition, operator returned by propose.\n    10Ôćĺ              List of rules to register with Proposer.\n    11ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n    12Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n    13Ôćĺ\n    14Ôćĺfrom agent.active_operators import (\n    15Ôćĺ    SolveTaskOperator,\n    16Ôćĺ    SubstateProgressOperator,\n    17Ôćĺ    SelectTargetOperator,\n    18Ôćĺ    CompareOperator,\n    19Ôćĺ    ExtractPatternOperator,\n    20Ôćĺ    GeneralizeOperator,\n    21Ôćĺ    DescendOperator,\n    22Ôćĺ    PredictOperator,\n    23Ôćĺ    SubmitOperator,\n    24Ôćĺ    VerifyOperator,\n    25Ôćĺ)\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ\n    28Ôćĺclass ProductionRule:\n    29Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    30Ôćĺ    [SOAR MANDATORY] Production Rule interface. condition + propose.\n    31Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] condition content, operator returned by propose.\n    32Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not modify WM in condition.\n    33Ôćĺ              Do not directly compute anything other than elaborated in condition.\n    34Ôćĺ              Do not execute operator in propose.\n    35Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    36Ôćĺ\n    37Ôćĺ    def __init__(self, name: str):\n    38Ôćĺ        self.name = name\n    39Ôćĺ\n    40Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n    41Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] Determine firing condition by reading only elaborated facts.\"\"\"\n    42Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\n    43Ôćĺ            f\"{self.__class__.__name__}.condition() must be implemented.\"\n    44Ôćĺ        )\n    45Ôćĺ\n    46Ôćĺ    def propose(self, wm) -> object:\n    47Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] Return an Operator instance when condition is met. Must not return None.\"\"\"\n    48Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\n    49Ôćĺ            f\"{self.__class__.__name__}.propose() must be implemented.\"\n    50Ôćĺ        )\n    51Ôćĺ\n    52Ôćĺ\n    53Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ Concrete ProductionRule implementations ÔÇö all [DESIGN FREE] ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ\n    54Ôćĺ\n    55Ôćĺ\n    56Ôćĺclass SolveTaskRule(ProductionRule):\n    57Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    58Ôćĺ    Proposes solve-task when S1 has ^current-task and no ^operator yet.\n    59Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    60Ôćĺ\n    61Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n    62Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"rule_solve_task\")\n    63Ôćĺ\n    64Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n    65Ôćĺ        if wm.depth > 0:\n    66Ôćĺ            return False\n    67Ôćĺ        state = wm.s1\n    68Ôćĺ        return bool(state.get(\"current-task\")) and \"operator\" not in state\n    69Ôćĺ\n    70Ôćĺ    def propose(self, wm):\n    71Ôćĺ        return SolveTaskOperator()\n    72Ôćĺ\n    73Ôćĺ\n    74Ôćĺclass SubstateNoChangeProgressRule(ProductionRule):\n    75Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    76Ôćĺ    After an operator no-change impasse opens in S2+, proposes a minimal concrete\n    77Ôćĺ    operator that can write a result to the superstate (S1).\n    78Ôćĺ    (To be replaced/branched with compare/collect in the future)\n    79Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    80Ôćĺ\n    81Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n    82Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"rule_substate_no_change_progress\")\n    83Ôćĺ\n    84Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n    85Ôćĺ        if wm.depth == 0:\n    86Ôćĺ            return False\n    87Ôćĺ        a = wm.active\n    88Ôćĺ        return (\n    89Ôćĺ            a.get(\"impasse\") == \"no-change\"\n    90Ôćĺ            and a.get(\"attribute\") == \"operator\"\n    91Ôćĺ            and \"operator\" not in a\n    92Ôćĺ        )\n    93Ôćĺ\n    94Ôćĺ    def propose(self, wm):\n    95Ôćĺ        return SubstateProgressOperator()\n    96Ôćĺ\n    97Ôćĺ\n    98Ôćĺclass SelectTargetRule(ProductionRule):\n    99Ôćĺ    \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] elaborated[\"needs_target_selection\"] Ôćĺ SelectTargetOperator.\"\"\"\n   100Ôćĺ\n   101Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   102Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"rule_select_target\")\n   103Ôćĺ\n   104Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   105Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"SelectTargetRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   106Ôćĺ\n   107Ôćĺ    def propose(self, wm):\n   108Ôćĺ        return SelectTargetOperator()\n   109Ôćĺ\n   110Ôćĺ\n   111Ôćĺclass CompareRule(ProductionRule):\n   112Ôćĺ    \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] elaborated[\"has_pending_comparison\"] Ôćĺ CompareOperator.\"\"\"\n   113Ôćĺ\n   114Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   115Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"rule_compare\")\n   116Ôćĺ\n   117Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   118Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"CompareRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   119Ôćĺ\n   120Ôćĺ    def propose(self, wm):\n   121Ôćĺ        return CompareOperator()\n   122Ôćĺ\n   123Ôćĺ\n   124Ôćĺclass ExtractPatternRule(ProductionRule):\n   125Ôćĺ    \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] elaborated[\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\"] Ôćĺ ExtractPatternOperator.\"\"\"\n   126Ôćĺ\n   127Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n   128Ôćĺ        super().__init__(\"rule_extract_pattern\")\n   129Ôćĺ\n   130Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   131Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"ExtractPatternRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   132Ôćĺ\n   133Ôćĺ    def propose(self, wm):\n   134Ôćĺ        return ExtractPatternOperator()\n   135Ôćĺ\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137Ôćĺclass GeneralizeRule(ProductionRule):\n   138Ôćĺ    \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] elaborated[\"ready_for_generalization\"] Ôćĺ GeneralizeOperator.\"\"\"\n   139Ô