{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SAedHS13T2kwiu3QbVwHRh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n     2Ôćĺwm_logger ÔÇö Utility for printing WorkingMemory state in SOAR triplet format.\n     3Ôćĺ\n     4ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n     5ÔćĺSOAR Working Memory Element (WME) format:\n     6Ôćĺ    (identifier ^attribute value)\n     7Ôćĺ\n     8Ôćĺ    identifier : S1=root, S2/S3...=substates, I1/I2...=auto-generated child nodes\n     9Ôćĺ    attribute  : field name\n    10Ôćĺ    value      : primitive or child node identifier\n    11Ôćĺ\n    12Ôćĺdiff colors (git diff style):\n    13Ôćĺ    Green background + white text  Ôćĺ  WME added/changed compared to previous call\n    14Ôćĺ    Red background + white text    Ôćĺ  WME removed compared to previous call\n    15Ôćĺ    Normal                         Ôćĺ  Unchanged WME\n    16Ôćĺ\n    17Ôćĺ    Comparison is based on path_key (e.g., S1/relations/pair_0/type) rather than\n    18Ôćĺ    auto-id (I1, I2...), so the semantic diff is computed accurately even if\n    19Ôćĺ    identifiers change.\n    20Ôćĺ\n    21ÔćĺUsage:\n    22Ôćĺ    from agent.wm_logger import print_wm_triplets, reset_wm_snapshot\n    23Ôćĺ    reset_wm_snapshot()                                 # Reset snapshot before task starts\n    24Ôćĺ    print_wm_triplets(wm, label=\"After: elaborate\", step=3)\n    25ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n    26Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n    27Ôćĺ\n    28Ôćĺfrom __future__ import annotations\n    29Ôćĺ\n    30Ôćĺimport itertools\n    31Ôćĺfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n    32Ôćĺfrom typing import Any\n    33Ôćĺ\n    34Ôćĺ\n    35Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ ANSI colors ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    36Ôćĺ\n    37Ôćĺ_GREEN_BG = \"\\033[42;37m\"   # Green background, white text (added/changed)\n    38Ôćĺ_RED_BG   = \"\\033[41;37m\"   # Red background, white text (removed)\n    39Ôćĺ_RESET    = \"\\033[0m\"\n    40Ôćĺ\n    41Ôćĺ# Output width: pad color background to match divider width.\n    42Ôćĺ_LINE_WIDTH = 62\n    43Ôćĺ\n    44Ôćĺ\n    45Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ Output constants ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    46Ôćĺ\n    47Ôćĺ_L1      = \"  \"       # depth 0 (root identifier S1/S2/WM) line indentation\n    48Ôćĺ_L2      = \"    \"     # depth 1 (direct children: I1, etc.) indentation\n    49Ôćĺ_L3      = \"      \"   # depth 2+ (grandchildren and below: I2, I3, etc.) indentation\n    50Ôćĺ_DIVIDER = \"ÔĽÉ\" * _LINE_WIDTH\n    51Ôćĺ\n    52Ôćĺ# S1/WM family identifier detection\n    53Ôćĺ_ROOT_IDS = {\"S1\", \"S2\", \"S3\", \"S4\", \"WM\"}\n    54Ôćĺ\n    55Ôćĺ# Maximum display length for string values\n    56Ôćĺ_MAX_STR_LEN = 80\n    57Ôćĺ\n    58Ôćĺ\n    59Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ WME data model ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    60Ôćĺ\n    61Ôćĺ@dataclass(frozen=True)\n    62Ôćĺclass _WME:\n    63Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    64Ôćĺ    A single Working Memory Element.\n    65Ôćĺ\n    66Ôćĺ    identifier : display node ID (S1, I1, ...)\n    67Ôćĺ    attribute  : field name\n    68Ôćĺ    value      : formatted value string\n    69Ôćĺ    path_key   : canonical path for diff comparison (e.g., \"S1/relations/pair_0/type\")\n    70Ôćĺ    is_root    : True if identifier is S1/WM family Ôćĺ L1 indentation\n    71Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    72Ôćĺ    identifier: str\n    73Ôćĺ    attribute:  str\n    74Ôćĺ    value:      str\n    75Ôćĺ    path_key:   str\n    76Ôćĺ    is_root:    bool\n    77Ôćĺ    depth:      int   # Depth relative to S1 (0=S1, 1=child, 2=grandchild...)\n    78Ôćĺ\n    79Ôćĺ\n    80Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ Module-level diff state ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    81Ôćĺ\n    82Ôćĺ# {path_key: _WME} ÔÇö Snapshot from the previous print_wm_triplets call\n    83Ôćĺ_prev_snap: dict[str, _WME] = {}\n    84Ôćĺ\n    85Ôćĺ\n    86Ôćĺdef reset_wm_snapshot(wm=None) -> None:\n    87Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    88Ôćĺ    Resets the diff snapshot.\n    89Ôćĺ\n    90Ôćĺ    wm=None  : Reset to empty snapshot Ôćĺ next print_wm_triplets call shows everything in green\n    91Ôćĺ    wm=<WM>  : Pre-fill snapshot with current WM state\n    92Ôćĺ               Ôćĺ next print_wm_triplets call shows no changes, all in normal color\n    93Ôćĺ\n    94Ôćĺ    Recommended usage pattern:\n    95Ôćĺ        # run_task.py ÔÇö Start diff from initial WM state\n    96Ôćĺ        build_wm_from_task(task, wm)\n    97Ôćĺ        reset_wm_snapshot(wm)              # Set initial state as baseline\n    98Ôćĺ        print_wm_triplets(wm, \"Initial WM state\")  # Print current state without colors\n    99Ôćĺ\n   100Ôćĺ        # active_agent.solve() ÔÇö Prevent previous state from mixing between tasks\n   101Ôćĺ        reset_wm_snapshot()                # Reset to empty state before task starts\n   102Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   103Ôćĺ    global _prev_snap\n   104Ôćĺ    if wm is not None:\n   105Ôćĺ        entries    = _wm_as_entries(wm)\n   106Ôćĺ        _prev_snap = {e.path_key: e for e in entries}\n   107Ôćĺ    else:\n   108Ôćĺ        _prev_snap = {}\n   109Ôćĺ\n   110Ôćĺ\n   111Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ Value formatting ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   112Ôćĺ\n   113Ôćĺdef _fmt(value: Any) -> str:\n   114Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Converts a primitive value to a SOAR display string.\"\"\"\n   115Ôćĺ    if value is None:\n   116Ôćĺ        return \"nil\"\n   117Ôćĺ    if isinstance(value, bool):\n   118Ôćĺ        return \"true\" if value else \"false\"\n   119Ôćĺ    if isinstance(value, str):\n   120Ôćĺ        # Preference symbols etc. ÔÇö single characters used bare in Soar\n   121Ôćĺ        if len(value) == 1 and value in \"+-!~<>\":\n   122Ôćĺ            return value\n   123Ôćĺ        # SOAR style: symbols without spaces/special chars are kept as-is; others are quoted.\n   124Ôćĺ        s = value if len(value) <= _MAX_STR_LEN else value[:_MAX_STR_LEN] + \"ÔÇŽ\"\n   125Ôćĺ        if s and all(ch.isalnum() or ch in (\"_\", \"-\", \".\") for ch in s):\n   126Ôćĺ            return s\n   127Ôćĺ        return f'\"{s}\"'\n   128Ôćĺ    return str(value)\n   129Ôćĺ\n   130Ôćĺ\n   131Ôćĺdef _is_grid(lst: list) -> bool:\n   132Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Determines whether the list looks like a 2D grid (array of integers or array of integer arrays).\"\"\"\n   133Ôćĺ    return bool(lst) and isinstance(lst[0], (int, list, tuple))\n   134Ôćĺ\n   135Ôćĺ\n   136Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ WME collection (recursive) ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   137Ôćĺ\n   138Ôćĺdef _collect(\n   139Ôćĺ    identifier:  str,\n   140Ôćĺ    attribute:   str,\n   141Ôćĺ    value:       Any,\n   142Ôćĺ    id_gen,\n   143Ôćĺ    out:         list[_WME],\n   144Ôćĺ    path_prefix: str,\n   145Ôćĺ    depth:       int,\n   146Ôćĺ    list_index:  int | None = None,\n   147Ôćĺ) -> None:\n   148Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   149Ôćĺ    Recursively expands a single (identifier, attribute, value) and appends _WME entries to out.\n   150Ôćĺ\n   151Ôćĺ    path_key generation rules:\n   152Ôćĺ        Normal dict field: \"{path_prefix}/{attribute}\"\n   153Ôćĺ        List item: \"{path_prefix}/{attribute}[{list_index}]\"\n   154Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   155Ôćĺ    if list_index is not None:\n   156Ôćĺ        path_key = f\"{path_prefix}/{attribute}[{list_index}]\"\n   157Ôćĺ    else:\n   158Ôćĺ        path_key = f\"{path_prefix}/{attribute}\"\n   159Ôćĺ\n   160Ôćĺ    is_root = identifier in _ROOT_IDS\n   161Ôćĺ\n   162Ôćĺ    if isinstance(value, dict):\n   163Ôćĺ        if not value:\n   164Ôćĺ            # Empty dict also gets a separate identifier (Ix) with just the link.\n   165Ôćĺ            # e.g., (I1 ^output-link I3) where I3 has no attributes yet.\n   166Ôćĺ            child_id = next(id_gen)\n   167Ôćĺ            out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, child_id, path_key, is_root, depth))\n   168Ôćĺ            return\n   169Ôćĺ        child_id = next(id_gen)\n   170Ôćĺ        out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, child_id, path_key, is_root, depth))\n   171Ôćĺ        for child_attr, child_val in value.items():\n   172Ôćĺ            _collect(child_id, child_attr, child_val, id_gen, out, path_key, depth + 1)\n   173Ôćĺ\n   174Ôćĺ    elif isinstance(value, list):\n   175Ôćĺ        if not value:\n   176Ôćĺ            out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, \"[]\", path_key, is_root, depth))\n   177Ôćĺ            return\n   178Ôćĺ        if _is_grid(value):\n   179Ôćĺ            first = value[0]\n   180Ôćĺ            ncols = len(first) if isinstance(first, (list, tuple)) else 1\n   181Ôćĺ            out.append(_WME(\n   182Ôćĺ                identifier, attribute, f\"<grid {len(value)}x{ncols}>\",\n   183Ôćĺ                path_key, is_root, depth,\n   184Ôćĺ            ))\n   185Ôćĺ            return\n   186Ôćĺ        # Normal list: recursively collect each item with index-based path_key\n   187Ôćĺ        for idx, item in enumerate(value):\n   188Ôćĺ            _collect(identifier, attribute, item, id_gen, out, path_prefix, depth, list_index=idx)\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ    else:\n   191Ôćĺ        out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, _fmt(value), path_key, is_root, depth))\n   192Ôćĺ\n   193Ôćĺ\n   194Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ WM Ôćĺ WME list conversion ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   195Ôćĺ\n   196Ôćĺdef _wm_as_entries(wm) -> list[_WME]:\n   197Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Converts the entire WorkingMemory to a list of _WME entries.\"\"\"\n   198Ôćĺ    id_gen = (f\"I{n}\" for n in itertools.count(1))\n   199Ôćĺ    out: list[_WME] = []\n   200Ôćĺ\n   201Ôćĺ    # S1 (root state)\n   202Ôćĺ    root = \"S1\"\n   203Ôćĺ    for attr, val in wm.s1.items():\n   204Ôćĺ        # Operator nodes and similar separate identifier nodes are treated as\n   205Ôćĺ        # independent identifiers rather than S1 attributes (e.g., O1).\n   206Ôćĺ        if isinstance(val, dict) and attr[:1].isalpha() and attr[0].isupper():\n   207Ôćĺ            for child_attr, child_val in val.items():\n   208Ôćĺ                _collect(attr, child_attr, child_val, id_gen, out, attr, depth=0)\n   209Ôćĺ            continue\n   210Ôćĺ        _collect(root, attr, val, id_gen, out, root, depth=0)\n   211Ôćĺ\n   212Ôćĺ    # task is an external reference outside WM (Python level), so only a summary is printed.\n   213Ôćĺ    # In SOAR style, environment input should go under io/input-link,\n   214Ôćĺ    # so this value is kept for debug purposes only.\n   215Ôćĺ    if getattr(wm, \"task\", None) is not None:\n   216Ôćĺ        summary = getattr(wm.task, \"task_hex\", repr(wm.task))\n   217Ôćĺ        out.append(_WME(root, \"task_ref\", f\"<task {summary}>\", f\"{root}/task_ref\", True, 0))\n   218Ôćĺ\n   219Ôćĺ    # S2, S3, ... (substate stack) ÔÇö Each substate is represented only as an independent Sx identifier.\n   220Ôćĺ    for depth, substate in enumerate(wm._substate_stack, start=2):\n   221Ôćĺ        sub = f\"S{depth}\"\n   222Ôćĺ        for attr, val in substate.items():\n   223Ôćĺ            # Same as S1: O* operator nodes are expanded as independent identifiers.\n   224Ôćĺ            if isinstance(val, dict) and attr[:1].isalpha() and attr[0].isupper():\n   225Ôćĺ                for child_attr, child_val in val.items():\n   226Ôćĺ                    _collect(attr, child_attr, child_val, id_gen, out, attr, depth=0)\n   227Ôćĺ                continue\n   228Ôćĺ            _collect(sub, attr, val, id_gen, out, sub, depth=0)\n   229Ôćĺ\n   230Ôćĺ    return out\n   231Ôćĺ\n   232Ôćĺ\n   233Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ Line formatting + colors ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   234Ôćĺ\n   235Ôćĺdef _indent_for_depth(depth: int) -> str:\n   236Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Returns the indentation string for the given depth value.\"\"\"\n   237Ôćĺ    if depth <= 0:\n   238Ôćĺ        return _L1\n   239Ôćĺ    if depth == 1:\n   240Ôćĺ        return _L2\n   241Ôćĺ    return _L3\n   242Ôćĺ\n   243Ôćĺ\n   244Ôćĺdef _render(entry: _WME) -> str:\n   245Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Converts a single _WME to a string in `  (S1 ^attr val)` format.\"\"\"\n   246Ôćĺ    indent = _L1 if entry.is_root else _L2\n   247Ôćĺ    return f\"{indent}({entry.identifier} ^{entry.attribute} {entry.value})\"\n   248Ôćĺ\n   249Ôćĺ\n   250Ôćĺdef _op_preference_map_current(current_entries: list[_WME]) -> dict[str, str]:\n   251Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Returns op-preference of O* nodes that exist only in the current WM (must not mix with removed WME list).\"\"\"\n   252Ôćĺ    d: dict[str, str] = {}\n   253Ôćĺ    for e in current_entries:\n   254Ôćĺ        if (\n   255Ôćĺ            len(e.identifier) >= 2\n   256Ôćĺ            and e.identifier[0] == \"O\"\n   257Ôćĺ            and e.identifier[1:].isdigit()\n   258Ôćĺ            and e.attribute == \"op-preference\"\n   259Ôćĺ        ):\n   260Ôćĺ            d[e.identifier] = e.value.strip()\n   261Ôćĺ    return d\n   262Ôćĺ\n   263Ôćĺ\n   264Ôćĺdef _grouped_lines(\n   265Ôćĺ    entries: list[_WME],\n   266Ôćĺ    *,\n   267Ôćĺ    op_preference_map: dict[str, str],\n   268Ôćĺ) -> list[tuple[str, str | None]]:\n   269Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   270Ôćĺ    Groups WMEs with the same identifier into a single block, similar to SOAR debug output style.\n   271Ôćĺ\n   272Ôćĺ    op_preference_map: Computed from current WM only (prevents contamination even if display_entries contains removed items).\n   273Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   274Ôćĺ    if not entries:\n   275Ôćĺ        return []\n   276Ôćĺ\n   277Ôćĺ    op_preference = op_preference_map\n   278Ôćĺ\n   279Ôćĺ    # Collect all WMEs by identifier (regardless of contiguity).\n   280Ôćĺ    by_id: dict[str, list[_WME]] = {}\n   281Ôćĺ    order: list[str] = []\n   282Ôćĺ    for e in entries:\n   283Ôćĺ        if e.identifier not in by_id:\n   284Ôćĺ            by_id[e.identifier] = []\n   285Ôćĺ            order.append(e.identifier)\n   286Ôćĺ        by_id[e.identifier].append(e)\n   287Ôćĺ\n   288Ôćĺ    # In O* blocks, ^op-preference is merged into the S1 line, so omit it as a separate line\n   289Ôćĺ    for oid, group in list(by_id.items()):\n   290Ôćĺ        if oid.startswith(\"O\") and len(oid) >= 2 and oid[1:].isdigit():\n   291Ôćĺ            by_id[oid] = [w for w in group if w.attribute != \"op-preference\"]\n   292Ôćĺ\n   293Ôćĺ    # Output order: S1, operators (O*), S2/S3/S4, WM, then remaining identifiers.\n   294Ôćĺ    def id_priority(ident: str) -> tuple[int, str]:\n   295Ôćĺ        if ident == \"S1\":\n   296Ôćĺ            return (0, ident)\n   297Ôćĺ        if ident.startswith(\"O\"):\n   298Ôćĺ            return (1, ident)\n   299Ôćĺ        if ident in {\"S2\", \"S3\", \"S4\"}:\n   300Ôćĺ            return (2, ident)\n   301Ôćĺ        if ident == \"WM\":\n   302Ôćĺ            return (3, ident)\n   303Ôćĺ        return (4, ident)\n   304Ôćĺ\n   305Ôćĺ    sorted_ids = sorted(order, key=id_priority)\n   306Ôćĺ\n   307Ôćĺ    # S1: proposal ^operator O* + followed by official ^operator O* (operator-application)\n   308Ôćĺ    _S1_ORDER = (\n   309Ôćĺ        \"type\",\n   310Ôćĺ        \"superstate\",\n   311Ôćĺ        \"io\",\n   312Ôćĺ        \"smem\",\n   313Ôćĺ        \"epmem\",\n   314Ôćĺ        \"current-task\",\n   315Ôćĺ        \"operator\",\n   316Ôćĺ        \"operator-application\",\n   317Ôćĺ    )\n   318Ôćĺ\n   319Ôćĺ    # S2, S3, ... (substate) ÔÇö smem Ôćĺ epmem fixed order\n   320Ôćĺ    _SUBSTATE_ORDER = (\n   321Ôćĺ        \"type\",\n   322Ôćĺ        \"superstate\",\n   323Ôćĺ        \"impasse\",\n   324Ôćĺ        \"choices\",\n   325Ôćĺ        \"attribute\",\n   326Ôćĺ        \"quiescence\",\n   327Ôćĺ        \"operator\",\n   328Ôćĺ        \"operator-application\",\n   329Ôćĺ        \"smem\",\n   330Ôćĺ        \"epmem\",\n   331Ôćĺ        \"item\",\n   332Ôćĺ        \"item-count\",\n   333Ôćĺ        \"non-numeric\",\n   334Ôćĺ        \"non-numeric-count\",\n   335Ôćĺ    )\n   336Ôćĺ\n   337Ôćĺ    def _s1_sort_key(e: _WME) -> tuple[int, str]:\n   338Ôćĺ        try:\n   339Ôćĺ            return (_S1_ORDER.index(e.attribute), e.attribute)\n   340Ôćĺ        except ValueError:\n   341Ôćĺ            return (len(_S1_ORDER), e.attribute)\n   342Ôćĺ\n   343Ôćĺ    def _substate_sort_key(e: _WME) -> tuple[int, str]:\n   344Ôćĺ        try:\n   345Ôćĺ            return (_SUBSTATE_ORDER.index(e.attribute), e.path_key)\n   346Ôćĺ        except ValueError:\n   347Ôćĺ            return (len(_SUBSTATE_ORDER), e.path_key)\n   348Ôćĺ\n   349Ôćĺ    def _is_substate_ident(ident: str) -> bool:\n   350Ôćĺ        return (\n   351Ôćĺ            len(ident) >= 2\n   352Ôćĺ            and ident[0] == \"S\"\n   353Ôćĺ            and ident != \"S1\"\n   354Ôćĺ            and ident[1:].isdigit()\n   355Ôćĺ        )\n   356Ôćĺ\n   357Ôćĺ    def _s1_show_attr(attr: str) -> str:\n   358Ôćĺ        return \"operator\" if attr == \"operator-application\" else attr\n   359Ôćĺ\n   360Ôćĺ    lines: list[tuple[str, str | None]] = []\n   361Ôćĺ\n   362Ôćĺ    for ident in sorted_ids:\n   363Ôćĺ        group = by_id[ident]\n   364Ôćĺ        if not group:\n   365Ôćĺ            continue\n   366Ôćĺ        if ident == \"S1\":\n   367Ôćĺ            group = sorted(group, key=_s1_sort_key)\n   368Ôćĺ        elif _is_substate_ident(ident):\n   369Ôćĺ            group = sorted(group, key=_substate_sort_key)\n   370Ôćĺ\n   371Ôćĺ        first = group[0]\n   372Ôćĺ        base_indent = _indent_for_depth(first.depth)\n   373Ôćĺ        cont_indent = base_indent + (\" \" * (len(ident) + 2))\n   374Ôćĺ\n   375Ôćĺ        def _proposal_suffix(e: _WME) -> str:\n   376Ôćĺ            if ident != \"S1\" or e.attribute != \"operator\":\n   377Ôćĺ                return \"\"\n   378Ôćĺ            sym = op_preference.get(e.value)\n   379Ôćĺ            return f\" {sym}\" if sym else \"\"\n   380Ôćĺ\n   381Ôćĺ        if ident == \"S1\":\n   382Ôćĺ            if len(group) == 1:\n   383Ôćĺ                e0 = group[0]\n   384Ôćĺ                a = _s1_show_attr(e0.attribute)\n   385Ôćĺ                text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{a} {e0.value}{_proposal_suffix(e0)})\"\n   386Ôćĺ                lines.append((text, e0.path_key))\n   387Ôćĺ            else:\n   388Ôćĺ                e0 = group[0]\n   389Ôćĺ                a0 = _s1_show_attr(e0.attribute)\n   390Ôćĺ                first_text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{a0} {e0.value}{_proposal_suffix(e0)}\"\n   391Ôćĺ                lines.append((first_text, e0.path_key))\n   392Ôćĺ                for k in range(1, len(group) - 1):\n   393Ôćĺ                    e = group[k]\n   394Ôćĺ                    a = _s1_show_attr(e.attribute)\n   395Ôćĺ                    mid = f\"{cont_indent}^{a} {e.value}{_proposal_suffix(e)}\"\n   396Ôćĺ                    lines.append((mid, e.path_key))\n   397Ôćĺ                el = group[-1]\n   398Ôćĺ                al = _s1_show_attr(el.attribute)\n   399Ôćĺ                last_text = f\"{cont_indent}^{al} {el.value}{_proposal_suffix(el)})\"\n   400Ôćĺ                lines.append((last_text, el.path_key))\n   401Ôćĺ            continue\n   402Ôćĺ\n   403Ôćĺ        if len(group) == 1:\n   404Ôćĺ            text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{first.attribute} {first.value})\"\n   405Ôćĺ            lines.append((text, first.path_key))\n   406Ôćĺ        else:\n   407Ôćĺ            first_text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{first.attribute} {first.value}\"\n   408Ôćĺ            lines.append((first_text, first.path_key))\n   409Ôćĺ            for k in range(1, len(group) - 1):\n   410Ôćĺ                e = group[k]\n   411Ôćĺ                lines.append((f\"{cont_indent}^{e.attribute} {e.value}\", e.path_key))\n   412Ôćĺ            last = group[-1]\n   413Ôćĺ            lines.append((f\"{cont_indent}^{last.attribute} {last.value})\", last.path_key))\n   414Ôćĺ\n   415Ôćĺ    return lines\n   416Ôćĺ\n   417Ôćĺdef _render_removed(entry: _WME) -> str:\n   418Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   419Ôćĺ    Displays a removed WME with path_key-based identifier.\n   420Ôćĺ\n   421Ôćĺ    Uses entry.identifier / attribute / depth information to\n   422Ôćĺ    maintain the same indentation as normal output.\n   423Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   424Ôćĺ    base_indent = _indent_for_depth(entry.depth)\n   425Ôćĺ    return f\"{base_indent}({entry.identifier} ^{entry.attribute} {entry.value})\"\n   426Ôćĺ\n   427Ôćĺ\n   428Ôćĺdef _colorize(text: str, ansi: str) -> str:\n   429Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Pads text to _LINE_WIDTH and wraps it with ANSI background color.\"\"\"\n   430Ôćĺ    padded = text.ljust(_LINE_WIDTH)\n   431Ôćĺ    return f\"{ansi}{padded}{_RESET}\"\n   432Ôćĺ\n   433Ôćĺ\n   434Ôćĺ# ÔöÇÔöÇ Public output function ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   435Ôćĺ\n   436Ôćĺdef print_wm_triplets(wm, label: str = \"\", step: int = 0) -> None:\n   437Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   438Ôćĺ    Prints the entire WorkingMemory state in SOAR triplet format + git diff style colors.\n   439Ôćĺ\n   440Ôćĺ    Output rules:\n   441Ôćĺ        Green background  Ôćĺ WME newly added or value changed compared to previous snapshot\n   442Ôćĺ        Red background    Ôćĺ WME that existed in previous snapshot but is now absent (removed section)\n   443Ôćĺ        Normal text       Ôćĺ Unchanged WME\n   444Ôćĺ\n   445Ôćĺ    On the first call, _prev_snap is empty so all items are shown in green.\n   446Ôćĺ    When the task changes, reset_wm_snapshot() must be called to reset the snapshot.\n   447Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   448Ôćĺ    global _prev_snap\n   449Ôćĺ\n   450Ôćĺ    entries   = _wm_as_entries(wm)\n   451Ôćĺ    curr_snap = {e.path_key: e for e in entries}\n   452Ôćĺ\n   453Ôćĺ    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Diff computation ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   454Ôćĺ    added_keys = {\n   455Ôćĺ        k for k, e in curr_snap.items()\n   456Ôćĺ        if k not in _prev_snap or _prev_snap[k].value != e.value\n   457Ôćĺ    }\n   458Ôćĺ    removed = {\n   459Ôćĺ        k: e for k, e in _prev_snap.items()\n   460Ôćĺ        if k not in curr_snap\n   461Ôćĺ    }\n   462Ôćĺ\n   463Ôćĺ    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Header ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   464Ôćĺ    header = f\"[Step {step}] {label}\" if label else f\"[Step {step}]\"\n   465Ôćĺ    print(_DIVIDER)\n   466Ôćĺ    print(f\"{_L1}{header}\")\n   467Ôćĺ    print(_DIVIDER)\n   468Ôćĺ\n   469Ôćĺ    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Print current state + removed items together (grouped by identifier) ÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   470Ôćĺ    # Display entries: current entries + removed entries (current takes priority for duplicate path_keys)\n   471Ôćĺ    display_entries: list[_WME] = list(entries)\n   472Ôćĺ    for k, e in removed.items():\n   473Ôćĺ        if k not in curr_snap:\n   474Ôćĺ            display_entries.append(e)\n   475Ôćĺ\n   476Ôćĺ    op_pref = _op_preference_map_current(entries)\n   477Ôćĺ    for text, path_key in _grouped_lines(display_entries, op_preference_map=op_pref):\n   478Ôćĺ        if path_key is not None:\n   479Ôćĺ            if path_key in removed:\n   480Ôćĺ                print(_colorize(text, _RED_BG))\n   481Ôćĺ                continue\n   482Ôćĺ            if path_key in added_keys:\n   483Ôćĺ                print(_colorize(text, _GREEN_BG))\n   484Ôćĺ                continue\n   485Ôćĺ        print(text)\n   486Ôćĺ\n   487Ôćĺ    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Footer ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   488Ôćĺ    print(_DIVIDER)\n   489Ôćĺ    print()\n   490Ôćĺ\n   491Ôćĺ    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Update snapshot ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n   492Ôćĺ    _prev_snap = curr_snap\n   493Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"228fd0fe-02da-4052-a2b4-e74389bf7110","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:33:16.648Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\agent\\wm_logger.py","content":"\"\"\"\nwm_logger ÔÇö Utility for printing WorkingMemory state in SOAR triplet format.\n\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\nSOAR Working Memory Element (WME) format:\n    (identifier ^attribute value)\n\n    identifier : S1=root, S2/S3...=substates, I1/I2...=auto-generated child nodes\n    attribute  : field name\n    value      : primitive or child node identifier\n\ndiff colors (git diff style):\n    Green background + white text  Ôćĺ  WME added/changed compared to previous call\n    Red background + white text    Ôćĺ  WME removed compared to previous call\n    Normal                         Ôćĺ  Unchanged WME\n\n    Comparison is based on path_key (e.g., S1/relations/pair_0/type) rather than\n    auto-id (I1, I2...), so the semantic diff is computed accurately even if\n    identifiers change.\n\nUsage:\n    from agent.wm_logger import print_wm_triplets, reset_wm_snapshot\n    reset_wm_snapshot()                                 # Reset snapshot before task starts\n    print_wm_triplets(wm, label=\"After: elaborate\", step=3)\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport itertools\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ ANSI colors ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\n_GREEN_BG = \"\\033[42;37m\"   # Green background, white text (added/changed)\n_RED_BG   = \"\\033[41;37m\"   # Red background, white text (removed)\n_RESET    = \"\\033[0m\"\n\n# Output width: pad color background to match divider width.\n_LINE_WIDTH = 62\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ Output constants ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\n_L1      = \"  \"       # depth 0 (root identifier S1/S2/WM) line indentation\n_L2      = \"    \"     # depth 1 (direct children: I1, etc.) indentation\n_L3      = \"      \"   # depth 2+ (grandchildren and below: I2, I3, etc.) indentation\n_DIVIDER = \"ÔĽÉ\" * _LINE_WIDTH\n\n# S1/WM family identifier detection\n_ROOT_IDS = {\"S1\", \"S2\", \"S3\", \"S4\", \"WM\"}\n\n# Maximum display length for string values\n_MAX_STR_LEN = 80\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ WME data model ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass _WME:\n    \"\"\"\n    A single Working Memory Element.\n\n    identifier : display node ID (S1, I1, ...)\n    attribute  : field name\n    value      : formatted value string\n    path_key   : canonical path for diff comparison (e.g., \"S1/relations/pair_0/type\")\n    is_root    : True if identifier is S1/WM family Ôćĺ L1 indentation\n    \"\"\"\n    identifier: str\n    attribute:  str\n    value:      str\n    path_key:   str\n    is_root:    bool\n    depth:      int   # Depth relative to S1 (0=S1, 1=child, 2=grandchild...)\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ Module-level diff state ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\n# {path_key: _WME} ÔÇö Snapshot from the previous print_wm_triplets call\n_prev_snap: dict[str, _WME] = {}\n\n\ndef reset_wm_snapshot(wm=None) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Resets the diff snapshot.\n\n    wm=None  : Reset to empty snapshot Ôćĺ next print_wm_triplets call shows everything in green\n    wm=<WM>  : Pre-fill snapshot with current WM state\n               Ôćĺ next print_wm_triplets call shows no changes, all in normal color\n\n    Recommended usage pattern:\n        # run_task.py ÔÇö Start diff from initial WM state\n        build_wm_from_task(task, wm)\n        reset_wm_snapshot(wm)              # Set initial state as baseline\n        print_wm_triplets(wm, \"Initial WM state\")  # Print current state without colors\n\n        # active_agent.solve() ÔÇö Prevent previous state from mixing between tasks\n        reset_wm_snapshot()                # Reset to empty state before task starts\n    \"\"\"\n    global _prev_snap\n    if wm is not None:\n        entries    = _wm_as_entries(wm)\n        _prev_snap = {e.path_key: e for e in entries}\n    else:\n        _prev_snap = {}\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ Value formatting ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\ndef _fmt(value: Any) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Converts a primitive value to a SOAR display string.\"\"\"\n    if value is None:\n        return \"nil\"\n    if isinstance(value, bool):\n        return \"true\" if value else \"false\"\n    if isinstance(value, str):\n        # Preference symbols etc. ÔÇö single characters used bare in Soar\n        if len(value) == 1 and value in \"+-!~<>\":\n            return value\n        # SOAR style: symbols without spaces/special chars are kept as-is; others are quoted.\n        s = value if len(value) <= _MAX_STR_LEN else value[:_MAX_STR_LEN] + \"ÔÇŽ\"\n        if s and all(ch.isalnum() or ch in (\"_\", \"-\", \".\") for ch in s):\n            return s\n        return f'\"{s}\"'\n    return str(value)\n\n\ndef _is_grid(lst: list) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Determines whether the list looks like a 2D grid (array of integers or array of integer arrays).\"\"\"\n    return bool(lst) and isinstance(lst[0], (int, list, tuple))\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ WME collection (recursive) ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\ndef _collect(\n    identifier:  str,\n    attribute:   str,\n    value:       Any,\n    id_gen,\n    out:         list[_WME],\n    path_prefix: str,\n    depth:       int,\n    list_index:  int | None = None,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Recursively expands a single (identifier, attribute, value) and appends _WME entries to out.\n\n    path_key generation rules:\n        Normal dict field: \"{path_prefix}/{attribute}\"\n        List item: \"{path_prefix}/{attribute}[{list_index}]\"\n    \"\"\"\n    if list_index is not None:\n        path_key = f\"{path_prefix}/{attribute}[{list_index}]\"\n    else:\n        path_key = f\"{path_prefix}/{attribute}\"\n\n    is_root = identifier in _ROOT_IDS\n\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        if not value:\n            # Empty dict also gets a separate identifier (Ix) with just the link.\n            # e.g., (I1 ^output-link I3) where I3 has no attributes yet.\n            child_id = next(id_gen)\n            out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, child_id, path_key, is_root, depth))\n            return\n        child_id = next(id_gen)\n        out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, child_id, path_key, is_root, depth))\n        for child_attr, child_val in value.items():\n            _collect(child_id, child_attr, child_val, id_gen, out, path_key, depth + 1)\n\n    elif isinstance(value, list):\n        if not value:\n            out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, \"[]\", path_key, is_root, depth))\n            return\n        if _is_grid(value):\n            first = value[0]\n            ncols = len(first) if isinstance(first, (list, tuple)) else 1\n            out.append(_WME(\n                identifier, attribute, f\"<grid {len(value)}x{ncols}>\",\n                path_key, is_root, depth,\n            ))\n            return\n        # Normal list: recursively collect each item with index-based path_key\n        for idx, item in enumerate(value):\n            _collect(identifier, attribute, item, id_gen, out, path_prefix, depth, list_index=idx)\n\n    else:\n        out.append(_WME(identifier, attribute, _fmt(value), path_key, is_root, depth))\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ WM Ôćĺ WME list conversion ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\ndef _wm_as_entries(wm) -> list[_WME]:\n    \"\"\"Converts the entire WorkingMemory to a list of _WME entries.\"\"\"\n    id_gen = (f\"I{n}\" for n in itertools.count(1))\n    out: list[_WME] = []\n\n    # S1 (root state)\n    root = \"S1\"\n    for attr, val in wm.s1.items():\n        # Operator nodes and similar separate identifier nodes are treated as\n        # independent identifiers rather than S1 attributes (e.g., O1).\n        if isinstance(val, dict) and attr[:1].isalpha() and attr[0].isupper():\n            for child_attr, child_val in val.items():\n                _collect(attr, child_attr, child_val, id_gen, out, attr, depth=0)\n            continue\n        _collect(root, attr, val, id_gen, out, root, depth=0)\n\n    # task is an external reference outside WM (Python level), so only a summary is printed.\n    # In SOAR style, environment input should go under io/input-link,\n    # so this value is kept for debug purposes only.\n    if getattr(wm, \"task\", None) is not None:\n        summary = getattr(wm.task, \"task_hex\", repr(wm.task))\n        out.append(_WME(root, \"task_ref\", f\"<task {summary}>\", f\"{root}/task_ref\", True, 0))\n\n    # S2, S3, ... (substate stack) ÔÇö Each substate is represented only as an independent Sx identifier.\n    for depth, substate in enumerate(wm._substate_stack, start=2):\n        sub = f\"S{depth}\"\n        for attr, val in substate.items():\n            # Same as S1: O* operator nodes are expanded as independent identifiers.\n            if isinstance(val, dict) and attr[:1].isalpha() and attr[0].isupper():\n                for child_attr, child_val in val.items():\n                    _collect(attr, child_attr, child_val, id_gen, out, attr, depth=0)\n                continue\n            _collect(sub, attr, val, id_gen, out, sub, depth=0)\n\n    return out\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ Line formatting + colors ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\ndef _indent_for_depth(depth: int) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Returns the indentation string for the given depth value.\"\"\"\n    if depth <= 0:\n        return _L1\n    if depth == 1:\n        return _L2\n    return _L3\n\n\ndef _render(entry: _WME) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Converts a single _WME to a string in `  (S1 ^attr val)` format.\"\"\"\n    indent = _L1 if entry.is_root else _L2\n    return f\"{indent}({entry.identifier} ^{entry.attribute} {entry.value})\"\n\n\ndef _op_preference_map_current(current_entries: list[_WME]) -> dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Returns op-preference of O* nodes that exist only in the current WM (must not mix with removed WME list).\"\"\"\n    d: dict[str, str] = {}\n    for e in current_entries:\n        if (\n            len(e.identifier) >= 2\n            and e.identifier[0] == \"O\"\n            and e.identifier[1:].isdigit()\n            and e.attribute == \"op-preference\"\n        ):\n            d[e.identifier] = e.value.strip()\n    return d\n\n\ndef _grouped_lines(\n    entries: list[_WME],\n    *,\n    op_preference_map: dict[str, str],\n) -> list[tuple[str, str | None]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Groups WMEs with the same identifier into a single block, similar to SOAR debug output style.\n\n    op_preference_map: Computed from current WM only (prevents contamination even if display_entries contains removed items).\n    \"\"\"\n    if not entries:\n        return []\n\n    op_preference = op_preference_map\n\n    # Collect all WMEs by identifier (regardless of contiguity).\n    by_id: dict[str, list[_WME]] = {}\n    order: list[str] = []\n    for e in entries:\n        if e.identifier not in by_id:\n            by_id[e.identifier] = []\n            order.append(e.identifier)\n        by_id[e.identifier].append(e)\n\n    # In O* blocks, ^op-preference is merged into the S1 line, so omit it as a separate line\n    for oid, group in list(by_id.items()):\n        if oid.startswith(\"O\") and len(oid) >= 2 and oid[1:].isdigit():\n            by_id[oid] = [w for w in group if w.attribute != \"op-preference\"]\n\n    # Output order: S1, operators (O*), S2/S3/S4, WM, then remaining identifiers.\n    def id_priority(ident: str) -> tuple[int, str]:\n        if ident == \"S1\":\n            return (0, ident)\n        if ident.startswith(\"O\"):\n            return (1, ident)\n        if ident in {\"S2\", \"S3\", \"S4\"}:\n            return (2, ident)\n        if ident == \"WM\":\n            return (3, ident)\n        return (4, ident)\n\n    sorted_ids = sorted(order, key=id_priority)\n\n    # S1: proposal ^operator O* + followed by official ^operator O* (operator-application)\n    _S1_ORDER = (\n        \"type\",\n        \"superstate\",\n        \"io\",\n        \"smem\",\n        \"epmem\",\n        \"current-task\",\n        \"operator\",\n        \"operator-application\",\n    )\n\n    # S2, S3, ... (substate) ÔÇö smem Ôćĺ epmem fixed order\n    _SUBSTATE_ORDER = (\n        \"type\",\n        \"superstate\",\n        \"impasse\",\n        \"choices\",\n        \"attribute\",\n        \"quiescence\",\n        \"operator\",\n        \"operator-application\",\n        \"smem\",\n        \"epmem\",\n        \"item\",\n        \"item-count\",\n        \"non-numeric\",\n        \"non-numeric-count\",\n    )\n\n    def _s1_sort_key(e: _WME) -> tuple[int, str]:\n        try:\n            return (_S1_ORDER.index(e.attribute), e.attribute)\n        except ValueError:\n            return (len(_S1_ORDER), e.attribute)\n\n    def _substate_sort_key(e: _WME) -> tuple[int, str]:\n        try:\n            return (_SUBSTATE_ORDER.index(e.attribute), e.path_key)\n        except ValueError:\n            return (len(_SUBSTATE_ORDER), e.path_key)\n\n    def _is_substate_ident(ident: str) -> bool:\n        return (\n            len(ident) >= 2\n            and ident[0] == \"S\"\n            and ident != \"S1\"\n            and ident[1:].isdigit()\n        )\n\n    def _s1_show_attr(attr: str) -> str:\n        return \"operator\" if attr == \"operator-application\" else attr\n\n    lines: list[tuple[str, str | None]] = []\n\n    for ident in sorted_ids:\n        group = by_id[ident]\n        if not group:\n            continue\n        if ident == \"S1\":\n            group = sorted(group, key=_s1_sort_key)\n        elif _is_substate_ident(ident):\n            group = sorted(group, key=_substate_sort_key)\n\n        first = group[0]\n        base_indent = _indent_for_depth(first.depth)\n        cont_indent = base_indent + (\" \" * (len(ident) + 2))\n\n        def _proposal_suffix(e: _WME) -> str:\n            if ident != \"S1\" or e.attribute != \"operator\":\n                return \"\"\n            sym = op_preference.get(e.value)\n            return f\" {sym}\" if sym else \"\"\n\n        if ident == \"S1\":\n            if len(group) == 1:\n                e0 = group[0]\n                a = _s1_show_attr(e0.attribute)\n                text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{a} {e0.value}{_proposal_suffix(e0)})\"\n                lines.append((text, e0.path_key))\n            else:\n                e0 = group[0]\n                a0 = _s1_show_attr(e0.attribute)\n                first_text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{a0} {e0.value}{_proposal_suffix(e0)}\"\n                lines.append((first_text, e0.path_key))\n                for k in range(1, len(group) - 1):\n                    e = group[k]\n                    a = _s1_show_attr(e.attribute)\n                    mid = f\"{cont_indent}^{a} {e.value}{_proposal_suffix(e)}\"\n                    lines.append((mid, e.path_key))\n                el = group[-1]\n                al = _s1_show_attr(el.attribute)\n                last_text = f\"{cont_indent}^{al} {el.value}{_proposal_suffix(el)})\"\n                lines.append((last_text, el.path_key))\n            continue\n\n        if len(group) == 1:\n            text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{first.attribute} {first.value})\"\n            lines.append((text, first.path_key))\n        else:\n            first_text = f\"{base_indent}({ident} ^{first.attribute} {first.value}\"\n            lines.append((first_text, first.path_key))\n            for k in range(1, len(group) - 1):\n                e = group[k]\n                lines.append((f\"{cont_indent}^{e.attribute} {e.value}\", e.path_key))\n            last = group[-1]\n            lines.append((f\"{cont_indent}^{last.attribute} {last.value})\", last.path_key))\n\n    return lines\n\ndef _render_removed(entry: _WME) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Displays a removed WME with path_key-based identifier.\n\n    Uses entry.identifier / attribute / depth information to\n    maintain the same indentation as normal output.\n    \"\"\"\n    base_indent = _indent_for_depth(entry.depth)\n    return f\"{base_indent}({entry.identifier} ^{entry.attribute} {entry.value})\"\n\n\ndef _colorize(text: str, ansi: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Pads text to _LINE_WIDTH and wraps it with ANSI background color.\"\"\"\n    padded = text.ljust(_LINE_WIDTH)\n    return f\"{ansi}{padded}{_RESET}\"\n\n\n# ÔöÇÔöÇ Public output function ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n\ndef print_wm_triplets(wm, label: str = \"\", step: int = 0) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Prints the entire WorkingMemory state in SOAR triplet format + git diff style colors.\n\n    Output rules:\n        Green background  Ôćĺ WME newly added or value changed compared to previous snapshot\n        Red background    Ôćĺ WME that existed in previous snapshot but is now absent (removed section)\n        Normal text       Ôćĺ Unchanged WME\n\n    On the first call, _prev_snap is empty so all items are shown in green.\n    When the task changes, reset_wm_snapshot() must be called to reset the snapshot.\n    \"\"\"\n    global _prev_snap\n\n    entries   = _wm_as_entries(wm)\n    curr_snap = {e.path_key: e for e in entries}\n\n    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Diff computation ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    added_keys = {\n        k for k, e in curr_snap.items()\n        if k not in _prev_snap or _prev_snap[k].value != e.value\n    }\n    removed = {\n        k: e for k, e in _prev_snap.items()\n        if k not in curr_snap\n    }\n\n    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Header ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    header = f\"[Step {step}] {label}\" if label else f\"[Step {step}]\"\n    print(_DIVIDER)\n    print(f\"{_L1}{header}\")\n    print(_DIVIDER)\n\n    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Print current state + removed items together (grouped by identifier) ÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    # Display entries: current entries + removed entries (current takes priority for duplicate path_keys)\n    display_entries: list[_WME] = list(entries)\n    for k, e in removed.items():\n        if k not in curr_snap:\n            display_entries.append(e)\n\n    op_pref = _op_preference_map_current(entries)\n    for text, path_key in _grouped_lines(display_entries, op_preference_map=op_pref):\n        if path_key is not None:\n            if path_key in removed:\n                print(_colorize(text, _RED_BG))\n                continue\n            if path_key in added_keys:\n                print(_colorize(text, _GREEN_BG))\n                continue\n        print(text)\n\n    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Footer ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    print(_DIVIDER)\n    print()\n\n    # ÔöÇÔöÇ Update snapshot ÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ #\n    _prev_snap = curr_snap\n","numLines":493,"startLine":1,"totalLines":493}}}
