{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013X7e9bL8G3vAQwzYN8eeQc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n     2ÔćĺWorkingMemory ÔÇö SOAR Working Memory.\n     3Ôćĺ\n     4ÔćĺOne of SOAR's four components.\n     5Ôćĺ  WM              ÔćÉ The entire current problem state (this file)\n     6Ôćĺ  Production Memory ÔćÉ elaboration_rules.py + rules.py\n     7Ôćĺ  Operators         ÔćÉ operators.py + active_operators.py\n     8Ôćĺ  Cycle             ÔćÉ cycle.py\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n    11Ôćĺ[SOAR MANDATORY] WM must exist.\n    12Ôćĺ                 All content is represented as (identifier, attribute, value) triplets.\n    13Ôćĺ                 Has an S1 (root) / S2 (substate) hierarchical structure.\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15ÔćĺDedicated dict slots such as comparison queue, relations, elaborated and WM helpers\n    16Ôćĺthat fill them are not provided.\n    17ÔćĺKnowledge is extended only by triplets/operators adding directly.\n    18ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n    19Ôćĺ\n    20ÔćĺÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ\n    21Ôćĺ[Design note ÔÇö Soar WM vs this class's fields]  (Reference for future cleanup)\n    22Ôćĺ\n    23ÔćĺConceptually, Soar WM is only a **set of WMEs**, and wme_records (+ timetag) correspond to that data.\n    24ÔćĺIn the Python implementation, **manager-role** fields are attached to operate on the set.\n    25Ôćĺ\n    26ÔćĺÔÇó Recommended to keep (nearly essential for engine/cycle)\n    27Ôćĺ  - _timetag_seq : Issues a unique, monotonically increasing timetag per WME (Soar 4 components)\n    28Ôćĺ  - _substate_stack : Substate stack on impasse ÔÇö rule evaluation order (superstate Ôćĺ most recent substate)\n    29Ôćĺ  - wme_timetags : Slot-level latest timetag index, since iterating the set alone can be slow\n    30Ôćĺ\n    31ÔćĺÔÇó Can be considered for removal/replacement during refactoring (convenience/cache)\n    32Ôćĺ  - s1 : S1 is merely an identifier in the WME graph, but keeping it as a \"root pointer\" simplifies implementation.\n    33Ôćĺ         Can be replaced with entry point search if using a pure graph.\n    34Ôćĺ  - task : Cache outside WM. In pure Soar, could be eliminated by accessing only through graph traversal like input-link.\n    35Ôćĺ\n    36ÔćĺThis class serves dual roles: \"WM data set\" + \"managing that set and driving the cycle\".\n    37ÔćĺÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ\n    38Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n    39Ôćĺ\n    40Ôćĺfrom __future__ import annotations\n    41Ôćĺ\n    42Ôćĺimport copy\n    43Ôćĺimport itertools\n    44Ôćĺfrom typing import Any\n    45Ôćĺ\n    46ÔćĺMAX_SUBSTATE_DEPTH: int = 2\n    47Ôćĺ\n    48Ôćĺ# Top-level slots to protect by default in SOAR style\n    49Ôćĺ_RESERVED_TOP_KEYS = frozenset({\"io\"})\n    50Ôćĺ\n    51Ôćĺ\n    52Ôćĺdef _is_operator_id(key: str) -> bool:\n    53Ôćĺ    return bool(key) and key[0] == \"O\" and key[1:].isdigit()\n    54Ôćĺ\n    55Ôćĺ\n    56Ôćĺclass _TrackedS1(dict):\n    57Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    58Ôćĺ    Records timetag when a top-level key is assigned to S1.\n    59Ôćĺ    When an operator node dict (O1/O2...) is inserted as a whole, records each sub-key separately.\n    60Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    61Ôćĺ\n    62Ôćĺ    __slots__ = (\"_wm\",)\n    63Ôćĺ\n    64Ôćĺ    def __init__(self, wm: \"WorkingMemory\", *args, **kwargs):\n    65Ôćĺ        super().__init__(*args, **kwargs)\n    66Ôćĺ        self._wm = wm\n    67Ôćĺ\n    68Ôćĺ    def __setitem__(self, key: str, value: Any) -> None:\n    69Ôćĺ        super().__setitem__(key, value)\n    70Ôćĺ        self._wm._record_wme(\"S1\", key, value)\n    71Ôćĺ        if isinstance(value, dict) and _is_operator_id(key):\n    72Ôćĺ            for sk, sv in value.items():\n    73Ôćĺ                self._wm._record_wme(key, sk, sv)\n    74Ôćĺ\n    75Ôćĺ\n    76Ôćĺclass WorkingMemory:\n    77Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    78Ôćĺ    [SOAR MANDATORY] WM class must exist.\n    79Ôćĺ                     S1/S2 hierarchy and triplet access interface (get/set) are SOAR protocol.\n    80Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    81Ôćĺ\n    82Ôćĺ    def __init__(self):\n    83Ôćĺ        # Soar timetag: integer that increases in WME creation order (not printed in logger)\n    84Ôćĺ        self._timetag_seq = itertools.count(1)\n    85Ôćĺ        # Full history (for debugger/print(wm.wme_records))\n    86Ôćĺ        self.wme_records: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    87Ôćĺ        # (identifier, attribute) -> latest timetag\n    88Ôćĺ        self.wme_timetags: dict[str, int] = {}\n    89Ôćĺ\n    90Ôćĺ        self.s1 = _TrackedS1(self)\n    91Ôćĺ        self.s1[\"type\"] = \"state\"\n    92Ôćĺ        self.s1[\"superstate\"] = None\n    93Ôćĺ        self.s1[\"io\"] = {\n    94Ôćĺ            \"input-link\": {},\n    95Ôćĺ            \"output-link\": {},\n    96Ôćĺ        }\n    97Ôćĺ        # States can be connected to semantic memory/episodic memory modules.\n    98Ôćĺ        # The detailed protocol is not yet defined, so only id is kept as placeholder.\n    99Ôćĺ        self.s1[\"smem\"] = {\"id\": \"SM1\"}\n   100Ôćĺ        self.s1[\"epmem\"] = {\"id\": \"E1\"}\n   101Ôćĺ\n   102Ôćĺ        self.task = None\n   103Ôćĺ        self._substate_stack: list = []\n   104Ôćĺ\n   105Ôćĺ    def _record_wme(self, identifier: str, attribute: str, value: Any) -> int:\n   106Ôćĺ        \"\"\"Internal: assigns a timetag to a triplet (output is not done by wm_logger).\"\"\"\n   107Ôćĺ        tt = next(self._timetag_seq)\n   108Ôćĺ        key = f\"{identifier}^{attribute}\"\n   109Ôćĺ        self.wme_timetags[key] = tt\n   110Ôćĺ        self.wme_records.append(\n   111Ôćĺ            {\n   112Ôćĺ                \"timetag\": tt,\n   113Ôćĺ                \"identifier\": identifier,\n   114Ôćĺ                \"attribute\": attribute,\n   115Ôćĺ                \"value\": value,\n   116Ôćĺ            }\n   117Ôćĺ        )\n   118Ôćĺ        return tt\n   119Ôćĺ\n   120Ôćĺ    def register_wme(self, identifier: str, attribute: str, value: Any) -> int:\n   121Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   122Ôćĺ        Used to manually record a timetag for paths other than S1 (e.g., input-link.task).\n   123Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   124Ôćĺ        return self._record_wme(identifier, attribute, value)\n   125Ôćĺ\n   126Ôćĺ    @property\n   127Ôćĺ    def active(self) -> dict:\n   128Ôćĺ        return self._substate_stack[-1] if self._substate_stack else self.s1\n   129Ôćĺ\n   130Ôćĺ    @property\n   131Ôćĺ    def depth(self) -> int:\n   132Ôćĺ        return len(self._substate_stack)\n   133Ôćĺ\n   134Ôćĺ    def get(self, key: str):\n   135Ôćĺ        return self.active.get(key)\n   136Ôćĺ\n   137Ôćĺ    def set(self, key: str, value):\n   138Ôćĺ        if key in _RESERVED_TOP_KEYS:\n   139Ôćĺ            raise ValueError(\n   140Ôćĺ                f\"WorkingMemory.set: Do not directly set '{key}'.\"\n   141Ôćĺ            )\n   142Ôćĺ        self.active[key] = value\n   143Ôćĺ\n   144Ôćĺ    def get_list(self, key: str) -> list:\n   145Ôćĺ        v = self.active.get(key)\n   146Ôćĺ        return v if isinstance(v, list) else []\n   147Ôćĺ\n   148Ôćĺ    def push_substate(\n   149Ôćĺ        self,\n   150Ôćĺ        impasse_type: str,\n   151Ôćĺ        attribute: str,\n   152Ôćĺ        *,\n   153Ôćĺ        items: list[str] | None = None,\n   154Ôćĺ        non_numeric_items: list[str] | None = None,\n   155Ôćĺ    ) -> bool:\n   156Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   157Ôćĺ        Creates a substate for impasse resolution.\n   158Ôćĺ\n   159Ôćĺ        impasse_type:\n   160Ôćĺ            - \"tie\"\n   161Ôćĺ            - \"no-change\"\n   162Ôćĺ            - \"conflict\"\n   163Ôćĺ            - \"constraint-failure\"\n   164Ôćĺ\n   165Ôćĺ        Follows a simplified Soar structure:\n   166Ôćĺ            (Sx ^type state\n   167Ôćĺ                ^impasse <type>\n   168Ôćĺ                ^choices <...>\n   169Ôćĺ                ^attribute <attribute>\n   170Ôćĺ                ^superstate Sy\n   171Ôćĺ                ^item ...              ; optional\n   172Ôćĺ                ^item-count N          ; optional\n   173Ôćĺ                ^non-numeric ...       ; optional for tie\n   174Ôćĺ                ^non-numeric-count M\n   175Ôćĺ                ^quiescence t\n   176Ôćĺ                ^reward-link Rk\n   177Ôćĺ                ^smem SMk\n   178Ôćĺ                ^epmem Ek\n   179Ôćĺ                ^svs SVk)\n   180Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n   181Ôćĺ        if len(self._substate_stack) >= MAX_SUBSTATE_DEPTH:\n   182Ôćĺ            return False\n   183Ôćĺ\n   184Ôćĺ        depth = len(self._substate_stack) + 2  # Starts from S2\n   185Ôćĺ        super_id = \"S1\" if depth == 2 else f\"S{depth-1}\"\n   186Ôćĺ\n   187Ôćĺ        # Default ^choices value by impasse type\n   188Ôćĺ        if impasse_type == \"tie\":\n   189Ôćĺ            choices = \"multiple\"\n   190Ôćĺ        elif impasse_type == \"conflict\":\n   191Ôćĺ            choices = \"multiple\"\n   192Ôćĺ        elif impasse_type == \"constraint-failure\":\n   193Ôćĺ            choices = \"constraint-failure\"\n   194Ôćĺ        else:\n   195Ôćĺ            # Default: includes no-change\n   196Ôćĺ            choices = \"none\"\n   197Ôćĺ\n   198Ôćĺ        sub: dict[str, Any] = {\n   199Ôćĺ            \"type\": \"state\",\n   200Ôćĺ            \"superstate\": super_id,\n   201Ôćĺ            \"impasse\": impasse_type,\n   202Ôćĺ            \"choices\": choices,\n   203Ôćĺ            \"attribute\": attribute,\n   204Ôćĺ            \"quiescence\": True,\n   205Ôćĺ            # Module links: keep only smem/epmem, omit reward-link and svs.\n   206Ôćĺ            \"smem\": {\"id\": f\"SM{depth}\"},\n   207Ôćĺ            \"epmem\": {\"id\": f\"E{depth}\"},\n   208Ôćĺ        }\n   209Ôćĺ\n   210Ôćĺ        if items:\n   211Ôćĺ            sub[\"item\"] = list(items)\n   212Ôćĺ            sub[\"item-count\"] = len(items)\n   213Ôćĺ\n   214Ôćĺ        if non_numeric_items:\n   215Ôćĺ            sub[\"non-numeric\"] = list(non_numeric_items)\n   216Ôćĺ            sub[\"non-numeric-count\"] = len(non_numeric_items)\n   217Ôćĺ\n   218Ôćĺ        self._substate_stack.append(sub)\n   219Ôćĺ        return True\n   220Ôćĺ\n   221Ôćĺ    def pop_substate(self, result: Any = None) -> None:\n   222Ôćĺ        if not self._substate_stack:\n   223Ôćĺ            return\n   224Ôćĺ        self._substate_stack.pop()\n   225Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"4a07245e-4fe0-4616-958b-786788acba94","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:33:16.657Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\agent\\wm.py","content":"\"\"\"\nWorkingMemory ÔÇö SOAR Working Memory.\n\nOne of SOAR's four components.\n  WM              ÔćÉ The entire current problem state (this file)\n  Production Memory ÔćÉ elaboration_rules.py + rules.py\n  Operators         ÔćÉ operators.py + active_operators.py\n  Cycle             ÔćÉ cycle.py\n\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n[SOAR MANDATORY] WM must exist.\n                 All content is represented as (identifier, attribute, value) triplets.\n                 Has an S1 (root) / S2 (substate) hierarchical structure.\n\nDedicated dict slots such as comparison queue, relations, elaborated and WM helpers\nthat fill them are not provided.\nKnowledge is extended only by triplets/operators adding directly.\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n\nÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ\n[Design note ÔÇö Soar WM vs this class's fields]  (Reference for future cleanup)\n\nConceptually, Soar WM is only a **set of WMEs**, and wme_records (+ timetag) correspond to that data.\nIn the Python implementation, **manager-role** fields are attached to operate on the set.\n\nÔÇó Recommended to keep (nearly essential for engine/cycle)\n  - _timetag_seq : Issues a unique, monotonically increasing timetag per WME (Soar 4 components)\n  - _substate_stack : Substate stack on impasse ÔÇö rule evaluation order (superstate Ôćĺ most recent substate)\n  - wme_timetags : Slot-level latest timetag index, since iterating the set alone can be slow\n\nÔÇó Can be considered for removal/replacement during refactoring (convenience/cache)\n  - s1 : S1 is merely an identifier in the WME graph, but keeping it as a \"root pointer\" simplifies implementation.\n         Can be replaced with entry point search if using a pure graph.\n  - task : Cache outside WM. In pure Soar, could be eliminated by accessing only through graph traversal like input-link.\n\nThis class serves dual roles: \"WM data set\" + \"managing that set and driving the cycle\".\nÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇÔöÇ\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport copy\nimport itertools\nfrom typing import Any\n\nMAX_SUBSTATE_DEPTH: int = 2\n\n# Top-level slots to protect by default in SOAR style\n_RESERVED_TOP_KEYS = frozenset({\"io\"})\n\n\ndef _is_operator_id(key: str) -> bool:\n    return bool(key) and key[0] == \"O\" and key[1:].isdigit()\n\n\nclass _TrackedS1(dict):\n    \"\"\"\n    Records timetag when a top-level key is assigned to S1.\n    When an operator node dict (O1/O2...) is inserted as a whole, records each sub-key separately.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    __slots__ = (\"_wm\",)\n\n    def __init__(self, wm: \"WorkingMemory\", *args, **kwargs):\n        super().__init__(*args, **kwargs)\n        self._wm = wm\n\n    def __setitem__(self, key: str, value: Any) -> None:\n        super().__setitem__(key, value)\n        self._wm._record_wme(\"S1\", key, value)\n        if isinstance(value, dict) and _is_operator_id(key):\n            for sk, sv in value.items():\n                self._wm._record_wme(key, sk, sv)\n\n\nclass WorkingMemory:\n    \"\"\"\n    [SOAR MANDATORY] WM class must exist.\n                     S1/S2 hierarchy and triplet access interface (get/set) are SOAR protocol.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self):\n        # Soar timetag: integer that increases in WME creation order (not printed in logger)\n        self._timetag_seq = itertools.count(1)\n        # Full history (for debugger/print(wm.wme_records))\n        self.wme_records: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n        # (identifier, attribute) -> latest timetag\n        self.wme_timetags: dict[str, int] = {}\n\n        self.s1 = _TrackedS1(self)\n        self.s1[\"type\"] = \"state\"\n        self.s1[\"superstate\"] = None\n        self.s1[\"io\"] = {\n            \"input-link\": {},\n            \"output-link\": {},\n        }\n        # States can be connected to semantic memory/episodic memory modules.\n        # The detailed protocol is not yet defined, so only id is kept as placeholder.\n        self.s1[\"smem\"] = {\"id\": \"SM1\"}\n        self.s1[\"epmem\"] = {\"id\": \"E1\"}\n\n        self.task = None\n        self._substate_stack: list = []\n\n    def _record_wme(self, identifier: str, attribute: str, value: Any) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Internal: assigns a timetag to a triplet (output is not done by wm_logger).\"\"\"\n        tt = next(self._timetag_seq)\n        key = f\"{identifier}^{attribute}\"\n        self.wme_timetags[key] = tt\n        self.wme_records.append(\n            {\n                \"timetag\": tt,\n                \"identifier\": identifier,\n                \"attribute\": attribute,\n                \"value\": value,\n            }\n        )\n        return tt\n\n    def register_wme(self, identifier: str, attribute: str, value: Any) -> int:\n        \"\"\"\n        Used to manually record a timetag for paths other than S1 (e.g., input-link.task).\n        \"\"\"\n        return self._record_wme(identifier, attribute, value)\n\n    @property\n    def active(self) -> dict:\n        return self._substate_stack[-1] if self._substate_stack else self.s1\n\n    @property\n    def depth(self) -> int:\n        return len(self._substate_stack)\n\n    def get(self, key: str):\n        return self.active.get(key)\n\n    def set(self, key: str, value):\n        if key in _RESERVED_TOP_KEYS:\n            raise ValueError(\n                f\"WorkingMemory.set: Do not directly set '{key}'.\"\n            )\n        self.active[key] = value\n\n    def get_list(self, key: str) -> list:\n        v = self.active.get(key)\n        return v if isinstance(v, list) else []\n\n    def push_substate(\n        self,\n        impasse_type: str,\n        attribute: str,\n        *,\n        items: list[str] | None = None,\n        non_numeric_items: list[str] | None = None,\n    ) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"\n        Creates a substate for impasse resolution.\n\n        impasse_type:\n            - \"tie\"\n            - \"no-change\"\n            - \"conflict\"\n            - \"constraint-failure\"\n\n        Follows a simplified Soar structure:\n            (Sx ^type state\n                ^impasse <type>\n                ^choices <...>\n                ^attribute <attribute>\n                ^superstate Sy\n                ^item ...              ; optional\n                ^item-count N          ; optional\n                ^non-numeric ...       ; optional for tie\n                ^non-numeric-count M\n                ^quiescence t\n                ^reward-link Rk\n                ^smem SMk\n                ^epmem Ek\n                ^svs SVk)\n        \"\"\"\n        if len(self._substate_stack) >= MAX_SUBSTATE_DEPTH:\n            return False\n\n        depth = len(self._substate_stack) + 2  # Starts from S2\n        super_id = \"S1\" if depth == 2 else f\"S{depth-1}\"\n\n        # Default ^choices value by impasse type\n        if impasse_type == \"tie\":\n            choices = \"multiple\"\n        elif impasse_type == \"conflict\":\n            choices = \"multiple\"\n        elif impasse_type == \"constraint-failure\":\n            choices = \"constraint-failure\"\n        else:\n            # Default: includes no-change\n            choices = \"none\"\n\n        sub: dict[str, Any] = {\n            \"type\": \"state\",\n            \"superstate\": super_id,\n            \"impasse\": impasse_type,\n            \"choices\": choices,\n            \"attribute\": attribute,\n            \"quiescence\": True,\n            # Module links: keep only smem/epmem, omit reward-link and svs.\n            \"smem\": {\"id\": f\"SM{depth}\"},\n            \"epmem\": {\"id\": f\"E{depth}\"},\n        }\n\n        if items:\n            sub[\"item\"] = list(items)\n            sub[\"item-count\"] = len(items)\n\n        if non_numeric_items:\n            sub[\"non-numeric\"] = list(non_numeric_items)\n            sub[\"non-numeric-count\"] = len(non_numeric_items)\n\n        self._substate_stack.append(sub)\n        return True\n\n    def pop_substate(self, result: Any = None) -> None:\n        if not self._substate_stack:\n            return\n        self._substate_stack.pop()\n","numLines":225,"startLine":1,"totalLines":225}}}
