{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Bj7aj6gkea48K1M9EaRqTR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n     2Ôćĺio ÔÇö SOAR I/O link management module.\n     3Ôćĺ\n     4ÔćĺSOAR perspective:\n     5Ôćĺ  - The architecture creates S1 and the ^io skeleton in the 0th decision cycle.\n     6Ôćĺ  - At the start of each execution cycle, the environment's input function is called\n     7Ôćĺ    to add the environment state (here, ARC task) as WMEs under WM's ^io ^input-link.\n     8Ôćĺ  - output-link is the channel where the agent records actions/results to send to the environment.\n     9Ôćĺ\n    10ÔćĺIn this project, WM is represented as Python dicts, so a serialized structure\n    11Ôćĺof the task is placed under input-link.\n    12Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n    13Ôćĺ\n    14Ôćĺfrom __future__ import annotations\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16Ôćĺ\n    17Ôćĺdef inject_arc_task(task, wm) -> None:\n    18Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    19Ôćĺ    Injects an ARC task under wm.s1['io']['input-link'].\n    20Ôćĺ\n    21Ôćĺ    Injection location (conceptual):\n    22Ôćĺ      (S1 ^io I1)\n    23Ôćĺ      (I1 ^input-link I2)\n    24Ôćĺ      (I2 ^task T1 ...)\n    25Ôćĺ\n    26Ôćĺ    In the implementation, task summary/grid content is placed in the input-link dict.\n    27Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    28Ôćĺ    io = wm.s1.get(\"io\")\n    29Ôćĺ    if not isinstance(io, dict) or \"input-link\" not in io:\n    30Ôćĺ        raise ValueError(\"io/input-link structure does not exist in WM.\")\n    31Ôćĺ\n    32Ôćĺ    in_link = io[\"input-link\"]\n    33Ôćĺ    # SOAR style: only a symbol pointing to the task is placed on input-link first.\n    34Ôćĺ    # Detailed example/test structure is extended later in the production/elaboration phase\n    35Ôćĺ    # by following current-task or through a separate input function.\n    36Ôćĺ    in_link[\"task\"] = task.task_hex\n    37Ôćĺ    wm.register_wme(\"input-link\", \"task\", task.task_hex)\n    38Ôćĺ\n    39Ôćĺ\n    40Ôćĺdef clear_input_link(wm) -> None:\n    41Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Clears the contents under ^input-link (for next execution cycle input refresh).\"\"\"\n    42Ôćĺ    io = wm.s1.get(\"io\")\n    43Ôćĺ    if not isinstance(io, dict) or \"input-link\" not in io:\n    44Ôćĺ        raise ValueError(\"io/input-link structure does not exist in WM.\")\n    45Ôćĺ    io[\"input-link\"].clear()\n    46Ôćĺ\n    47Ôćĺ\n    48Ôćĺdef clear_output_link(wm) -> None:\n    49Ôćĺ    \"\"\"Clears the contents under ^output-link (reset after reflecting to environment).\"\"\"\n    50Ôćĺ    io = wm.s1.get(\"io\")\n    51Ôćĺ    if not isinstance(io, dict) or \"output-link\" not in io:\n    52Ôćĺ        raise ValueError(\"io/output-link structure does not exist in WM.\")\n    53Ôćĺ    io[\"output-link\"].clear()\n    54Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"ffa1cd9a-2a3b-4606-a090-82b7d53f2dbf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:33:16.871Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\agent\\io.py","content":"\"\"\"\nio ÔÇö SOAR I/O link management module.\n\nSOAR perspective:\n  - The architecture creates S1 and the ^io skeleton in the 0th decision cycle.\n  - At the start of each execution cycle, the environment's input function is called\n    to add the environment state (here, ARC task) as WMEs under WM's ^io ^input-link.\n  - output-link is the channel where the agent records actions/results to send to the environment.\n\nIn this project, WM is represented as Python dicts, so a serialized structure\nof the task is placed under input-link.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\n\ndef inject_arc_task(task, wm) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    Injects an ARC task under wm.s1['io']['input-link'].\n\n    Injection location (conceptual):\n      (S1 ^io I1)\n      (I1 ^input-link I2)\n      (I2 ^task T1 ...)\n\n    In the implementation, task summary/grid content is placed in the input-link dict.\n    \"\"\"\n    io = wm.s1.get(\"io\")\n    if not isinstance(io, dict) or \"input-link\" not in io:\n        raise ValueError(\"io/input-link structure does not exist in WM.\")\n\n    in_link = io[\"input-link\"]\n    # SOAR style: only a symbol pointing to the task is placed on input-link first.\n    # Detailed example/test structure is extended later in the production/elaboration phase\n    # by following current-task or through a separate input function.\n    in_link[\"task\"] = task.task_hex\n    wm.register_wme(\"input-link\", \"task\", task.task_hex)\n\n\ndef clear_input_link(wm) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Clears the contents under ^input-link (for next execution cycle input refresh).\"\"\"\n    io = wm.s1.get(\"io\")\n    if not isinstance(io, dict) or \"input-link\" not in io:\n        raise ValueError(\"io/input-link structure does not exist in WM.\")\n    io[\"input-link\"].clear()\n\n\ndef clear_output_link(wm) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Clears the contents under ^output-link (reset after reflecting to environment).\"\"\"\n    io = wm.s1.get(\"io\")\n    if not isinstance(io, dict) or \"output-link\" not in io:\n        raise ValueError(\"io/output-link structure does not exist in WM.\")\n    io[\"output-link\"].clear()\n","numLines":54,"startLine":1,"totalLines":54}}}
