{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DuMertp6VbSsJgSo21jESo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n     2Ôćĺelaboration_rules ÔÇö Elaboration rules for SOAR Production Memory.\n     3Ôćĺ\n     4ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n     5Ôćĺ[SOAR MANDATORY] The Elaborate phase runs first in every cycle.\n     6Ôćĺ                 Elaborator applies rules repeatedly until fixed-point.\n     7Ôćĺ                 ElaborationRule interface (condition Ôćĺ derive) is SOAR protocol.\n     8Ôćĺ\n     9Ôćĺ[DESIGN FREE] What derived facts to create (entire rule content).\n    10Ôćĺ              Names and values of derived facts.\n    11Ôćĺ              List of rules to register with Elaborator.\n    12ÔćĺÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n    13Ôćĺ\"\"\"\n    14Ôćĺ\n    15Ôćĺ\n    16Ôćĺclass ElaborationRule:\n    17Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    18Ôćĺ    [SOAR MANDATORY] Elaboration rule interface.\n    19Ôćĺ                     When condition(wm) Ôćĺ True, derive(wm) returns a derived fact dict.\n    20Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] Content of condition, content of derive (defined by concrete rule classes).\n    21Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Do not modify WM ÔÇö only return derived fact dict.\n    22Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    23Ôćĺ\n    24Ôćĺ    def __init__(self, name: str):\n    25Ôćĺ        self.name = name\n    26Ôćĺ\n    27Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n    28Ôćĺ        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] Firing condition. WM modification prohibited.\"\"\"\n    29Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\n    30Ôćĺ            f\"{self.__class__.__name__}.condition() must be implemented.\"\n    31Ôćĺ        )\n    32Ôćĺ\n    33Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n    34Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n    35Ôćĺ        [DESIGN FREE] Return derived fact dict. Format: {fact_name: value}\n    36Ôćĺ        MUST NOT: Do not return empty dict.\n    37Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n    38Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\n    39Ôćĺ            f\"{self.__class__.__name__}.derive() must be implemented.\"\n    40Ôćĺ        )\n    41Ôćĺ\n    42Ôćĺ\n    43Ôćĺclass Elaborator:\n    44Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    45Ôćĺ    [SOAR MANDATORY] Engine that repeatedly applies a list of ElaborationRules until fixed-point.\n    46Ôćĺ                     Initializes and fills wm.active[\"elaborated\"].\n    47Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] List of rules to register (determined in build_elaborator).\n    48Ôćĺ    MUST NOT: Force termination when MAX_ITERATIONS is exceeded (infinite loop prevention).\n    49Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n    50Ôćĺ\n    51Ôćĺ    MAX_ITERATIONS: int = 20\n    52Ôćĺ\n    53Ôćĺ    def __init__(self, rules: list):\n    54Ôćĺ        self._rules = rules\n    55Ôćĺ\n    56Ôćĺ    def run(self, wm):\n    57Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n    58Ôćĺ        [SOAR MANDATORY] Fixed-point iteration engine ÔÇö called every cycle.\n    59Ôćĺ        \"\"\"\n    60Ôćĺ        iterations = 0\n    61Ôćĺ        while iterations < self.MAX_ITERATIONS:\n    62Ôćĺ            iterations += 1\n    63Ôćĺ            changed = False\n    64Ôćĺ\n    65Ôćĺ            state = wm.active\n    66Ôćĺ\n    67Ôćĺ            # --- i-support style handling: if task disappears from input-link,\n    68Ôćĺ            #     current-task that depended on it is also automatically removed. ---\n    69Ôćĺ            io = state.get(\"io\") or {}\n    70Ôćĺ            in_link = io.get(\"input-link\") or {}\n    71Ôćĺ            if \"task\" not in in_link and \"current-task\" in state:\n    72Ôćĺ                del state[\"current-task\"]\n    73Ôćĺ                changed = True\n    74Ôćĺ\n    75Ôćĺ            # --- Apply each rule (add/update derived facts) ---\n    76Ôćĺ            for rule in self._rules:\n    77Ôćĺ                try:\n    78Ôćĺ                    if not rule.condition(wm):\n    79Ôćĺ                        continue\n    80Ôćĺ                    delta = rule.derive(wm)\n    81Ôćĺ                except NotImplementedError:\n    82Ôćĺ                    # Skip rules that are not yet implemented.\n    83Ôćĺ                    continue\n    84Ôćĺ                if not delta:\n    85Ôćĺ                    continue\n    86Ôćĺ                for key, value in delta.items():\n    87Ôćĺ                    # Do not treat as a change if the value is the same.\n    88Ôćĺ                    if key in state and state[key] == value:\n    89Ôćĺ                        continue\n    90Ôćĺ                    state[key] = value\n    91Ôćĺ                    changed = True\n    92Ôćĺ\n    93Ôćĺ            if not changed:\n    94Ôćĺ                break\n    95Ôćĺ\n    96Ôćĺ\n    97Ôćĺ# ------------------------------------------------------------------ #\n    98Ôćĺ# Concrete ElaborationRule implementations ÔÇö all [DESIGN FREE]\n    99Ôćĺ# ------------------------------------------------------------------ #\n   100Ôćĺ\n   101Ôćĺ\n   102Ôćĺclass InputTaskToStateRule(ElaborationRule):\n   103Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   104Ôćĺ    SOAR rule:\n   105Ôćĺ      sp { elaborate*input*task\n   106Ôćĺ        (state <s> ^io.input-link <in>)\n   107Ôćĺ        (<in> ^task <t>)\n   108Ôćĺ      -->\n   109Ôćĺ        (<s> ^current-task <t>)\n   110Ôćĺ      }\n   111Ôćĺ\n   112Ôćĺ    In this implementation:\n   113Ôćĺ      - When wm.s1['io']['input-link']['task'] exists and\n   114Ôćĺ      - wm.s1 does not yet have a 'current-task' slot,\n   115Ôćĺ        derive(wm) is interpreted as returning {\"current-task\": <task_dict>}.\n   116Ôćĺ\n   117Ôćĺ    The actual method of attaching to WM is determined by the Elaborator.run implementation.\n   118Ôćĺ    (e.g., wm.active.update(derive_dict))\n   119Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   120Ôćĺ\n   121Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   122Ôćĺ        state = wm.active\n   123Ôćĺ        io = state.get(\"io\") or {}\n   124Ôćĺ        in_link = io.get(\"input-link\") or {}\n   125Ôćĺ        has_task = \"task\" in in_link\n   126Ôćĺ        has_current = \"current-task\" in state\n   127Ôćĺ        return bool(has_task and not has_current)\n   128Ôćĺ\n   129Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   130Ôćĺ        state = wm.active\n   131Ôćĺ        io = state.get(\"io\") or {}\n   132Ôćĺ        in_link = io.get(\"input-link\") or {}\n   133Ôćĺ        task_val = in_link.get(\"task\")\n   134Ôćĺ        if task_val is None:\n   135Ôćĺ            # Defensive handling, though this should only be called when condition is True.\n   136Ôćĺ            return {}\n   137Ôćĺ        return {\"current-task\": task_val}\n   138Ôćĺ\n   139Ôćĺclass NeedsTargetSelectionRule(ElaborationRule):\n   140Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   141Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] When comparison_agenda has unprocessed items and\n   142Ôćĺ                   pending_comparisons is empty,\n   143Ôćĺ                   derives elaborated[\"needs_target_selection\"] = True.\n   144Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   145Ôćĺ\n   146Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   147Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"NeedsTargetSelectionRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   148Ôćĺ\n   149Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   150Ôćĺ        return {\"needs_target_selection\": True}\n   151Ôćĺ\n   152Ôćĺ\n   153Ôćĺclass HasPendingComparisonRule(ElaborationRule):\n   154Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   155Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] When there are items in the pending_comparisons queue,\n   156Ôćĺ                   derives elaborated[\"has_pending_comparison\"] = True.\n   157Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   158Ôćĺ\n   159Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   160Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"HasPendingComparisonRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   161Ôćĺ\n   162Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   163Ôćĺ        return {\"has_pending_comparison\": True}\n   164Ôćĺ\n   165Ôćĺ\n   166Ôćĺclass AllComparisonsDoneRule(ElaborationRule):\n   167Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   168Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] When both agenda and pending are empty and\n   169Ôćĺ                   all required comparisons exist in relations,\n   170Ôćĺ                   derives elaborated[\"all_comparisons_done\"] = True.\n   171Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   172Ôćĺ\n   173Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   174Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"AllComparisonsDoneRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   175Ôćĺ\n   176Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   177Ôćĺ        return {\"all_comparisons_done\": True}\n   178Ôćĺ\n   179Ôćĺ\n   180Ôćĺclass ReadyForPatternExtractionRule(ElaborationRule):\n   181Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   182Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] When all_comparisons_done == True AND\n   183Ôćĺ                   both invariants and diff_patterns are empty,\n   184Ôćĺ                   derives elaborated[\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\"] = True.\n   185Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   186Ôćĺ\n   187Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   188Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"ReadyForPatternExtractionRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   189Ôćĺ\n   190Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   191Ôćĺ        return {\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\": True}\n   192Ôćĺ\n   193Ôćĺ\n   194Ôćĺclass ReadyForGeneralizationRule(ElaborationRule):\n   195Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   196Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] When both invariants and diff_patterns are populated,\n   197Ôćĺ                   derives elaborated[\"ready_for_generalization\"] = True.\n   198Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   199Ôćĺ\n   200Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   201Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"ReadyForGeneralizationRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   202Ôćĺ\n   203Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   204Ôćĺ        return {\"ready_for_generalization\": True}\n   205Ôćĺ\n   206Ôćĺ\n   207Ôćĺclass ReadyForPredictionRule(ElaborationRule):\n   208Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   209Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] When active_rules is not empty and\n   210Ôćĺ                   there is at least one pending test subgoal,\n   211Ôćĺ                   derives elaborated[\"ready_for_prediction\"] = True.\n   212Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   213Ôćĺ\n   214Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   215Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"ReadyForPredictionRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   216Ôćĺ\n   217Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   218Ôćĺ        return {\"ready_for_prediction\": True}\n   219Ôćĺ\n   220Ôćĺ\n   221Ôćĺclass AllOutputsFoundRule(ElaborationRule):\n   222Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   223Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] When all test subgoals are solved,\n   224Ôćĺ                   derives elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"] = True.\n   225Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   226Ôćĺ\n   227Ôćĺ    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n   228Ôćĺ        raise NotImplementedError(\"AllOutputsFoundRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n   229Ôćĺ\n   230Ôćĺ    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n   231Ôćĺ        return {\"all_outputs_found\": True}\n   232Ôćĺ\n   233Ôćĺ\n   234Ôćĺdef build_elaborator() -> Elaborator:\n   235Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   236Ôćĺ    [DESIGN FREE] Which ElaborationRules to register.\n   237Ôćĺ                   Created at ActiveSoarAgent.solve() call time.\n   238Ôćĺ    \"\"\"\n   239Ôćĺ    # Currently only the rule that pulls the input task into state is activated.\n   240Ôćĺ    rules = [\n   241Ôćĺ        InputTaskToStateRule(\"elaborate_input_task\"),\n   242Ôćĺ        # NeedsTargetSelectionRule(\"needs_target_selection\"),\n   243Ôćĺ        # HasPendingComparisonRule(\"has_pending_comparison\"),\n   244Ôćĺ        # AllComparisonsDoneRule(\"all_comparisons_done\"),\n   245Ôćĺ        # ReadyForPatternExtractionRule(\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\"),\n   246Ôćĺ        # ReadyForGeneralizationRule(\"ready_for_generalization\"),\n   247Ôćĺ        # ReadyForPredictionRule(\"ready_for_prediction\"),\n   248Ôćĺ        # AllOutputsFoundRule(\"all_outputs_found\"),\n   249Ôćĺ    ]\n   250Ôćĺ    return Elaborator(rules)\n   251Ôćĺ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"a02ca98a-09b6-4e00-92b7-d8048f341700","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:33:17.134Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\agent\\elaboration_rules.py","content":"\"\"\"\nelaboration_rules ÔÇö Elaboration rules for SOAR Production Memory.\n\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n[SOAR MANDATORY] The Elaborate phase runs first in every cycle.\n                 Elaborator applies rules repeatedly until fixed-point.\n                 ElaborationRule interface (condition Ôćĺ derive) is SOAR protocol.\n\n[DESIGN FREE] What derived facts to create (entire rule content).\n              Names and values of derived facts.\n              List of rules to register with Elaborator.\nÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöüÔöü\n\"\"\"\n\n\nclass ElaborationRule:\n    \"\"\"\n    [SOAR MANDATORY] Elaboration rule interface.\n                     When condition(wm) Ôćĺ True, derive(wm) returns a derived fact dict.\n    [DESIGN FREE] Content of condition, content of derive (defined by concrete rule classes).\n    MUST NOT: Do not modify WM ÔÇö only return derived fact dict.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, name: str):\n        self.name = name\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"[DESIGN FREE] Firing condition. WM modification prohibited.\"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\n            f\"{self.__class__.__name__}.condition() must be implemented.\"\n        )\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"\n        [DESIGN FREE] Return derived fact dict. Format: {fact_name: value}\n        MUST NOT: Do not return empty dict.\n        \"\"\"\n        raise NotImplementedError(\n            f\"{self.__class__.__name__}.derive() must be implemented.\"\n        )\n\n\nclass Elaborator:\n    \"\"\"\n    [SOAR MANDATORY] Engine that repeatedly applies a list of ElaborationRules until fixed-point.\n                     Initializes and fills wm.active[\"elaborated\"].\n    [DESIGN FREE] List of rules to register (determined in build_elaborator).\n    MUST NOT: Force termination when MAX_ITERATIONS is exceeded (infinite loop prevention).\n    \"\"\"\n\n    MAX_ITERATIONS: int = 20\n\n    def __init__(self, rules: list):\n        self._rules = rules\n\n    def run(self, wm):\n        \"\"\"\n        [SOAR MANDATORY] Fixed-point iteration engine ÔÇö called every cycle.\n        \"\"\"\n        iterations = 0\n        while iterations < self.MAX_ITERATIONS:\n            iterations += 1\n            changed = False\n\n            state = wm.active\n\n            # --- i-support style handling: if task disappears from input-link,\n            #     current-task that depended on it is also automatically removed. ---\n            io = state.get(\"io\") or {}\n            in_link = io.get(\"input-link\") or {}\n            if \"task\" not in in_link and \"current-task\" in state:\n                del state[\"current-task\"]\n                changed = True\n\n            # --- Apply each rule (add/update derived facts) ---\n            for rule in self._rules:\n                try:\n                    if not rule.condition(wm):\n                        continue\n                    delta = rule.derive(wm)\n                except NotImplementedError:\n                    # Skip rules that are not yet implemented.\n                    continue\n                if not delta:\n                    continue\n                for key, value in delta.items():\n                    # Do not treat as a change if the value is the same.\n                    if key in state and state[key] == value:\n                        continue\n                    state[key] = value\n                    changed = True\n\n            if not changed:\n                break\n\n\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------ #\n# Concrete ElaborationRule implementations ÔÇö all [DESIGN FREE]\n# ------------------------------------------------------------------ #\n\n\nclass InputTaskToStateRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    SOAR rule:\n      sp { elaborate*input*task\n        (state <s> ^io.input-link <in>)\n        (<in> ^task <t>)\n      -->\n        (<s> ^current-task <t>)\n      }\n\n    In this implementation:\n      - When wm.s1['io']['input-link']['task'] exists and\n      - wm.s1 does not yet have a 'current-task' slot,\n        derive(wm) is interpreted as returning {\"current-task\": <task_dict>}.\n\n    The actual method of attaching to WM is determined by the Elaborator.run implementation.\n    (e.g., wm.active.update(derive_dict))\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        state = wm.active\n        io = state.get(\"io\") or {}\n        in_link = io.get(\"input-link\") or {}\n        has_task = \"task\" in in_link\n        has_current = \"current-task\" in state\n        return bool(has_task and not has_current)\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        state = wm.active\n        io = state.get(\"io\") or {}\n        in_link = io.get(\"input-link\") or {}\n        task_val = in_link.get(\"task\")\n        if task_val is None:\n            # Defensive handling, though this should only be called when condition is True.\n            return {}\n        return {\"current-task\": task_val}\n\nclass NeedsTargetSelectionRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] When comparison_agenda has unprocessed items and\n                   pending_comparisons is empty,\n                   derives elaborated[\"needs_target_selection\"] = True.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"NeedsTargetSelectionRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        return {\"needs_target_selection\": True}\n\n\nclass HasPendingComparisonRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] When there are items in the pending_comparisons queue,\n                   derives elaborated[\"has_pending_comparison\"] = True.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"HasPendingComparisonRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        return {\"has_pending_comparison\": True}\n\n\nclass AllComparisonsDoneRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] When both agenda and pending are empty and\n                   all required comparisons exist in relations,\n                   derives elaborated[\"all_comparisons_done\"] = True.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"AllComparisonsDoneRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        return {\"all_comparisons_done\": True}\n\n\nclass ReadyForPatternExtractionRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] When all_comparisons_done == True AND\n                   both invariants and diff_patterns are empty,\n                   derives elaborated[\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\"] = True.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"ReadyForPatternExtractionRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        return {\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\": True}\n\n\nclass ReadyForGeneralizationRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] When both invariants and diff_patterns are populated,\n                   derives elaborated[\"ready_for_generalization\"] = True.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"ReadyForGeneralizationRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        return {\"ready_for_generalization\": True}\n\n\nclass ReadyForPredictionRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] When active_rules is not empty and\n                   there is at least one pending test subgoal,\n                   derives elaborated[\"ready_for_prediction\"] = True.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"ReadyForPredictionRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        return {\"ready_for_prediction\": True}\n\n\nclass AllOutputsFoundRule(ElaborationRule):\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] When all test subgoals are solved,\n                   derives elaborated[\"all_outputs_found\"] = True.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def condition(self, wm) -> bool:\n        raise NotImplementedError(\"AllOutputsFoundRule.condition() not implemented.\")\n\n    def derive(self, wm) -> dict:\n        return {\"all_outputs_found\": True}\n\n\ndef build_elaborator() -> Elaborator:\n    \"\"\"\n    [DESIGN FREE] Which ElaborationRules to register.\n                   Created at ActiveSoarAgent.solve() call time.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Currently only the rule that pulls the input task into state is activated.\n    rules = [\n        InputTaskToStateRule(\"elaborate_input_task\"),\n        # NeedsTargetSelectionRule(\"needs_target_selection\"),\n        # HasPendingComparisonRule(\"has_pending_comparison\"),\n        # AllComparisonsDoneRule(\"all_comparisons_done\"),\n        # ReadyForPatternExtractionRule(\"ready_for_pattern_extraction\"),\n        # ReadyForGeneralizationRule(\"ready_for_generalization\"),\n        # ReadyForPredictionRule(\"ready_for_prediction\"),\n        # AllOutputsFoundRule(\"all_outputs_found\"),\n    ]\n    return Elaborator(rules)\n","numLines":251,"startLine":1,"totalLines":251}}}
